<inglise>Chapter 4 </inglise>
<eesti>Mootors&otilde;iduki juhtimine </eesti>
<inglise>Driving Motor Vehicles </inglise>
<eesti>&sect; 17. </eesti>
<inglise>&sect; 17. </inglise>
<eesti>Mootors&otilde;idukijuhilt n&otilde;utavad dokumendid </eesti>
<inglise>Documents required from drivers of motor vehicles </inglise>
<eesti>(1) Juhil peavad mootors&otilde;iduki juhtimisel olema kaasas juhiluba v&otilde;i muu juhtimis&otilde;igust t&otilde;endav dokument, mootors&otilde;iduki ja selle haagise registreerimistunnistus, kohustusliku liikluskindlustuse poliis v&otilde;i t&otilde;end kindlustuslepingu s&otilde;lmimisest vabastamise kohta ja muud dokumendid, kui seda n&otilde;uab seadus. </eesti>
<inglise>(1) When driving a motor vehicle, a driver shall carry a driving licence or other document certifying his or her right to drive, the registration certificate of the motor vehicle and its trailer, a motor third party liability insurance policy or a certificate concerning exemption from the requirement to enter into an insurance contract and other documents if so demanded by law. </inglise>
<eesti>(2) Kui s&otilde;iduki eest tuleb tasuda mootors&otilde;idukimaksu v&otilde;i raskeveokimaksu, peab juhil olema kaasas vastava maksu tasumist t&otilde;endav dokument. </eesti>
<inglise>(2) If motor vehicle tax or heavy goods vehicle tax is to be paid for a vehicle, the driver shall carry a document certifying payment of the corresponding tax. </inglise>
<eesti>(3) Juhil, kes ei ole s&otilde;iduki omanik ja kelle nimi ei ole kantud s&otilde;iduki registreerimistunnistusele s&otilde;iduki kasutajana, peab kaasas olema omaniku poolt v&auml;ljaantud s&otilde;iduki kasutamise volikiri, kui omanik ei ole kaass&otilde;itja. </eesti>
<inglise>(3) A driver who is not the owner of the vehicle and whose name is not entered on the registration certificate of the vehicle as the user of the vehicle shall carry an authorisation document to use the vehicle, issued by the owner, unless the owner is a passenger in the vehicle. </inglise>
<eesti>Volikiri v&otilde;ib olla lihtkirjalik, kui seadus ei n&otilde;ua notariaalselt t&otilde;estatud volikirja. </eesti>
<inglise>The authorisation document may be unattested unless a notarised authorisation document is demanded by law. </inglise>
<eesti>(4) K&auml;esoleva paragrahvi l&otilde;ikes 3 nimetatud volikiri peab olema notariaalselt t&otilde;estatud, kui juht soovib Eestis registreeritud s&otilde;iduautoga v&otilde;i kuni 3500-kilogrammise registrimassiga veoautoga s&otilde;ita Eestist v&auml;lja. </eesti>
<inglise>(4) The authorisation document specified in subsection (3) of this section shall be notarised if the driver wishes to leave Estonia in an automobile which is registered in Estonia or in a truck which is registered in Estonia and which has a permissible maximum mass of 3500 kilograms. </inglise>
<eesti>(5) K&auml;esoleva paragrahvi l&otilde;ikes 4 nimetatud notariaalselt t&otilde;estatud volikirja asendab s&otilde;iduki rendileping, kui s&otilde;iduki omanik ja rendileandja on Eesti &auml;riregistrisse kantud juriidiline isik, kelle p&otilde;hikirjaliseks tegevuseks on s&otilde;idukite rentimine. </eesti>
<inglise>(5) The notarised authorisation document specified in subsection (4) of this section may be substituted by the commercial lease contract of the vehicle if the owner and the commercial lessor of the vehicle are legal persons who are entered in the Estonian commercial register and whose activities, as specified in their articles of association, include the commercial leasing of vehicles. </inglise>
<eesti>Rendileping peab sisaldama k&auml;esoleva seaduse &sect; 18 l&otilde;ikes 1 nimetatud andmeid. </eesti>
<inglise>The commercial lease contract shall contain the information specified in subsection 18 (1) of this Act. </inglise>
<eesti>(6) Veoste veol peab lisaks k&auml;esolevas paragrahvis nimetatule olema kaasas veodokumendid ja eriveoste veol ka juhile antud tunnistus vastava v&auml;lja&otilde;ppe l&auml;bimise ja s&otilde;iduki eriveole lubamise kohta koosk&otilde;las autoveoseadusega (RT I 2000, 54, 346). </eesti>
<inglise>(6) Upon the carriage of goods, transport documents in addition to the documents specified in this section shall be carried and, upon the carriage of special goods, a certificate issued to the driver to certify that he or she has undergone the corresponding training and that the vehicle is permitted to carry special goods in accordance with the Road Transport Act (RT I 2000, 54, 346) shall also be carried. </inglise>
<eesti>(7) K&auml;esoleva seaduse &sect; 23 l&otilde;igetes 2 ja 3 nimetatud isikul, kes on B-kategooria autos piiratud juhtimis&otilde;igusega juhi k&otilde;rval v&otilde;i on piiratud juhtimis&otilde;igusega juhi poolt juhitava R-kategooria mootors&otilde;iduki vahetus l&auml;heduses, peab olema kaasas vastava kategooria s&otilde;iduki juhtimise &otilde;igust t&otilde;endav juhiluba. </eesti>
<inglise>(7) A person specified in subsections 23 (2) or (3) of this Act who is in a category B automobile next to a driver with a limited right to drive or who is in the immediate vicinity of a category R motor vehicle being driven by a driver with a limited right to drive shall carry a driving licence certifying that he or she has the right to drive vehicles of the corresponding category. </inglise>
<eesti>(8) Isikul, kes juhib mootors&otilde;idukit koosk&otilde;las k&auml;esoleva seaduse &sect; 32 l&otilde;igetega 1 ja 2, peab &otilde;ppes&otilde;idu ajal olema kaasas koolituskursuse &otilde;pingukaart v&otilde;i tunnistus. </eesti>
<inglise>(8) A person who drives a motor vehicle in accordance with subsections 32 (1) or (2) of this Act shall carry a learner's form or learner's certificate during driving lessons. </inglise>
<eesti>(9) K&auml;esoleva seaduse &sect; 32 l&otilde;ikes 1 nimetatud mootors&otilde;idukijuhi &otilde;petajal ja l&otilde;ikes 2 nimetatud juhendajal peab olema kaasas juhiluba ja vastav tunnistus. </eesti>
<inglise>(9) An instructor of a driver specified in subsection 32 (1) of this Act and an instructor specified in subsection 32 (2) of this Act shall carry a driving licence and a corresponding certificate. </inglise>
<eesti>&sect; 18. </eesti>
<inglise>&sect; 18. </inglise>
<eesti>S&otilde;iduki kasutamise volikiri </eesti>
<inglise>Authorisation document to use vehicle </inglise>
<eesti>(1) S&otilde;iduki kasutamise volikirjas peavad sisalduma j&auml;rgmised andmed: </eesti>
<inglise>(1) An authorisation document to use a vehicle shall contain the following information: </inglise>
<eesti>1) koostamise koht ja kuup&auml;ev; </eesti>
<inglise>1) the place and date of preparation; </inglise>
<eesti>2) s&otilde;iduki omaniku nimi ja aadress; </eesti>
<inglise>2) the name and address of the owner of the vehicle; </inglise>
<eesti>3) s&otilde;iduki mark ja mudel, valmistajatehase t&auml;his; </eesti>
<inglise>3) the make and model of the vehicle, and the vehicle identification number; </inglise>
<eesti>4) registreerimistunnistuse number ja riikliku registreerimism&auml;rgi andmed; </eesti>
<inglise>4) the number of the registration certificate and information on the state registration number; </inglise>
<eesti>5) s&otilde;iduki kasutaja nimi ja aadress ning juhiloa number. </eesti>
<inglise>5) the name and address of the user of the vehicle and the number of his or her driving licence. </inglise>
<eesti>(2) Volikiri peab olema kinnitatud volitaja allkirjaga. </eesti>
<inglise>(2) An authorisation document shall bear the signature of the person authorising the use of the vehicle. </inglise>
<eesti>&sect; 19. </eesti>
<inglise>&sect; 19. </inglise>
<eesti>Erin&otilde;uded mootors&otilde;idukijuhi s&otilde;idu- ja puhkeajale </eesti>
<inglise>Special requirements for driving and rest time of drivers of motor vehicles </inglise>
<eesti>(1) S&otilde;itjaid vedava &uuml;le &uuml;heksa istekohaga (kaasa arvatud juhi koht) v&otilde;i veost vedava &uuml;le 3500-kilogrammise registrimassiga, haagisega v&otilde;i haagiseta mootors&otilde;iduki juhi s&otilde;idu- ja puhkeaja kestuse ning arvestamise korra kehtestab Vabariigi Valitsus. </eesti>
<inglise>(1) The duration of driving and rest time for drivers of motor vehicles which carry passengers and which have more than nine seats (including the driver's seat), and of motor vehicles, with or without a trailer, which carry goods and which have a permissible maximum mass exceeding 3500 kilograms, and the procedure for calculation thereof shall be established by the Government of the Republic. </inglise>
<eesti>(2) K&auml;esoleva paragrahvi l&otilde;ikes 1 nimetatud mootors&otilde;iduki juhi s&otilde;idu- ja puhkeaja arvestus toimub s&otilde;idumeeriku salvestuslehtede j&auml;rgi. </eesti>
<inglise>(2) The driving and rest time of drivers of motor vehicles, as specified in subsection (1) of this section, shall be calculated according to tachograph record sheets. </inglise>
<eesti>Salvestuslehti peab s&auml;ilitama v&auml;hemalt viimase 12 kuu kohta. </eesti>
<inglise>Record sheets shall be preserved for at least the last twelve months. </inglise>
<eesti>(3) K&auml;esoleva paragrahvi l&otilde;ikes 1 nimetatud mootors&otilde;iduki juhi s&otilde;idu- ja puhkeaja kohta kehtestatud n&otilde;uete j&auml;rgimist kontrollivad: </eesti>
<inglise>(3) Compliance with the requirements established concerning the driving and rest time of drivers of motor vehicles, as specified in subsection (1) of this section, shall be supervised: </inglise>
<eesti>1) liikluses politseiametnikud, abipolitseinikud ja teised selleks seadusega volitatud isikud; </eesti>
<inglise>1) in traffic, by police officers, special constables and other persons so authorised by law; </inglise>
<eesti>2) mootors&otilde;iduki valdaja juures T&ouml;&ouml;inspektsiooni ametnikud. </eesti>
<inglise>2) at the possessors of motor vehicles, by officials of the Labour Inspectorate. </inglise>
<eesti>(4) K&auml;esoleva paragrahvi l&otilde;ikes 1 nimetatud mootors&otilde;iduki juhil peavad s&otilde;idu ajal olema kaasas ja ta peab esitama kontrollijale jooksva n&auml;dala salvestuslehed ja eelmise n&auml;dala viimase p&auml;eva salvestuslehe, millal ta juhtis mootors&otilde;idukit. </eesti>
<inglise>(4) While driving, drivers of motor vehicles specified in subsection (1) of this section shall carry, and if necessary show to an inspector, the record sheets for the given week and the record sheet for the last day of the previous week on which they drove a motor vehicle. </inglise>
<eesti>&sect; 20. </eesti>
<inglise>&sect; 20. </inglise>
<eesti>S&otilde;iduki juhtimise keeld </eesti>
<inglise>Prohibition on driving vehicles </inglise>
<eesti>(1) Mootors&otilde;idukit ei v&otilde;i juhtida isik, kellel ei ole vastava kategooria mootors&otilde;iduki juhtimise &otilde;igust. </eesti>
<inglise>(1) A person shall not drive a motor vehicle if he or she does not have the right to drive motor vehicles of the corresponding category. </inglise>
<eesti>(2) Mootors&otilde;iduki omanik, valdaja v&otilde;i juht ei v&otilde;i lubada mootors&otilde;idukit juhtima isikut v&otilde;i anda juhtimist &uuml;le isikule, kellel puudub vastava kategooria mootors&otilde;iduki juhtimise &otilde;igus v&otilde;i kes ei vasta k&auml;esoleva paragrahvi l&otilde;igetes 3, 4 v&otilde;i 7 nimetatud n&otilde;uetele. </eesti>
<inglise>(2) The owner, possessor or driver of a motor vehicle shall not permit a person who does not have the right to drive vehicles of the corresponding category or who does not meet the requirements specified in subsections (3), (4) or (7) of this section to drive the motor vehicle and shall not entrust the driving of the motor vehicle to such person. </inglise>
<eesti>(3) Juht ei v&otilde;i olla joobeseisundis. </eesti>
<inglise>(3) A driver shall not be in a state of intoxication. </inglise>
<eesti>Joobeseisund on alkoholi, narkootilise v&otilde;i ps&uuml;hhotroopse aine tarvitamisest p&otilde;hjustatud terviseseisund, mis avaldub h&auml;iritud v&otilde;i muutunud kehalistes v&otilde;i ps&uuml;&uuml;hilistes funktsioonides ja reaktsioonides. </eesti>
<inglise>A state of intoxication is a state of health which is caused by the consumption of alcohol, narcotic drugs or psychotropic substances and which results in disturbed or changed bodily or mental functions and reactions. </inglise>
<eesti>(4) Alkoholisisaldus &uuml;hes liitris juhi v&auml;ljahingatavas &otilde;hus ei v&otilde;i olla 0,1 milligrammi v&otilde;i rohkem v&otilde;i alkoholisisaldus juhi veres 0,2 promilli v&otilde;i rohkem. </eesti>
<inglise>(4) The alcohol content in breath exhaled by a driver shall not be 0.1 milligrams or more of alcohol in one litre of breath, or the alcohol content in the blood of a driver shall not be 0.2 milligrams or more of alcohol in 1 millilitre of blood. </inglise>
<eesti>Juhil on &otilde;igus p&auml;rast tema v&auml;ljahingatava &otilde;hu alkoholisisalduse kontrollimist n&otilde;uda alkoholisisalduse m&auml;&auml;ramist veres. </eesti>
<inglise>After the alcohol content in the breath exhaled by the driver has been measured, he or she has the right to request measurement of the alcohol content in his or her blood. </inglise>
<eesti>(5) Kui juht p&otilde;geneb s&uuml;ndmuskohalt v&otilde;i keeldub alkoholisisalduse kontrollimisest tema v&auml;ljahingatavas &otilde;hus v&otilde;i veres v&otilde;i joobeseisundi tuvastamisest v&otilde;i p&auml;rast nimetatud kontrollimise v&otilde;i tuvastamise ettepanekut tarvitab aineid, mis v&otilde;ivad esile kutsuda joovet, loetakse kirjeldatud tegevus k&auml;esoleva paragrahvi l&otilde;igetes 3 ja 4 nimetatud n&otilde;uete rikkumiseks. </eesti>
<inglise>(5) If a driver leaves the scene of an accident or refuses to allow the alcohol content in his or her breath or blood to be measured or his or her state of intoxication to be ascertained, or if, after it is suggested that the alcohol content in his or her breath be measured or his or her state of intoxication ascertained, he or she consumes substances which may induce intoxication, the actions of the driver are deemed to be a violation of the requirements specified in subsections (3) and (4) of this section. </inglise>
<eesti>(6) Joobeseisundi tuvastamise ja joobeastme m&auml;&auml;ramise korra ning joobeastme m&auml;&auml;ramise otsuse vaidlustamise korra kehtestab Vabariigi Valitsus. </eesti>
<inglise>(6) The procedure for ascertaining a state of intoxication and determining a degree of intoxication and the procedure for contesting a decision on the determination of a degree of intoxication shall be established by the Government of the Republic. </inglise>
<eesti>(7) Juht ei v&otilde;i olla sellises haigus- v&otilde;i v&auml;simusseisundis, mis takistab liiklusolude t&auml;pset tajumist ning liikluseeskirja n&otilde;uete k&otilde;rvalekaldumatut t&auml;itmist. </eesti>
<inglise>(7) A driver shall not be so ill or fatigued as to prevent his or her clear perception of traffic conditions or to prevent him or her from complying fully with the Traffic Code. </inglise>
<eesti>Haigus- ja v&auml;simusseisundi tuvastamise korra kehtestab Vabariigi Valitsus. </eesti>
<inglise>The procedure for ascertaining the state of illness or fatigue shall be established by the Government of the Republic. </inglise>
<eesti>5. peat&uuml;kk </eesti>
<inglise>Chapter 5 </inglise>
<eesti>Mootors&otilde;iduki juhtimise &otilde;igus </eesti>
<inglise>Right to Drive Motor Vehicles </inglise>
<eesti>&sect; 21. </eesti>
<inglise>&sect; 21. </inglise>
<eesti>Mootors&otilde;idukite kategooriad </eesti>
<inglise>Categories of motor vehicles </inglise>
<eesti>(1) Mootors&otilde;iduki juhtimise &otilde;iguse (edaspidi juhtimis&otilde;iguse) seisukohalt jagunevad autod ja mootorrattad p&otilde;hikategooriatesse A (mootorrattad), B, C, D (autod), BE, CE, DE (autorongid) ja nende alamkategooriatesse A1, B1, C1, D1, C1E ja D1E. </eesti>
<inglise>(1) In terms of the right to drive motor vehicles (hereinafter right to drive), automobiles and motorcycles are divided into the main categories A (motorcycles), B, C, D (automobiles), BE, CE, DE (road trains) and their subcategories A1, B1, C1, D1, C1E and D1E. </inglise>
<eesti>(2) Juhtimis&otilde;iguse seisukohalt jagunevad ratastraktorid ja liikurmasinad Eestis kehtivatesse kategooriatesse T ja R. </eesti>
<inglise>(2) In terms of the right to drive, wheeled tractors and non-road mobile machinery are divided into categories T and R which apply in Estonia. </inglise>
<eesti>(3) Mootors&otilde;idukite ja nende haagiste kategooriatesse jaotamise tehnilised andmed on toodud k&auml;esoleva seaduse lisas 1. </eesti>
<inglise>(3) Technical information on the division of motor vehicles and their trailers into categories is set out in Annex 1 to this Act. </inglise>
<eesti>&sect; 22. </eesti>
<inglise>&sect; 22. </inglise>
<eesti>Juhtimis&otilde;igus </eesti>
<inglise>Right to drive </inglise>
<eesti>(1) Mootors&otilde;idukit v&otilde;ib juhtida isik, kellel on vastava kategooria mootors&otilde;iduki juhtimise &otilde;igus. </eesti>
<inglise>(1) A motor vehicle may be driven by a person who has the right to drive vehicles of the corresponding category. </inglise>
<eesti>(2) A-, B-, C- v&otilde;i D-kategooria mootors&otilde;iduki juhil on &otilde;igus juhtida vastavalt ka A1-, B1-, C1- v&otilde;i D1-alamkategooria mootors&otilde;idukit. </eesti>
<inglise>(2) Drivers of motor vehicles in categories A, B, C or D also have the right to drive motor vehicles in subcategories A1, B1, C1 or D1 respectively. </inglise>
<eesti>(3) C1E-, CE-, D1E- v&otilde;i DE-kategooria autorongi juhtimise &otilde;igus lubab juhtida ka BE-kategooria autorongi. </eesti>
<inglise>(3) The right to drive road trains in categories C1E, CE, D1E or DE also grants the right to drive road trains in category BE. </inglise>
<eesti>CE-kategooria autorongi juhtimise &otilde;igus lubab juhtida ka DE-kategooria autorongi, kui isikul on D-kategooria auto juhiluba. </eesti>
<inglise>The right to drive road trains in category CE also grants the right to drive road trains in category DE if the driver holds a category D driving licence. </inglise>
<eesti>(4) C1E-alamkategooria autorongi juhtimise &otilde;igus lubab juhtida ka D1E-alamkategooria autorongi, kui isikul on D1-alamkategooria auto juhiluba. </eesti>
<inglise>(4) The right to drive road trains in category C1E also grants the right to drive road trains in category D1E if the driver holds a driving licence for subcategory D1. </inglise>
<eesti>(5) DE-kategooria autorongi juhtimise &otilde;igus lubab juhtida ka C1E-alamkategooria autorongi, kui isikul on C1-alamkategooria auto juhiluba. </eesti>
<inglise>(5) The right to drive road trains in category DE also grants the right to drive road trains in category C1E if the driver holds a driving licence for subcategory C1. </inglise>
<eesti>(6) T-kategooria mootors&otilde;idukit v&otilde;ib juhtida ka isik, kellel on C- v&otilde;i D-kategooria, C1- v&otilde;i D1-alamkategooria auto juhtimise &otilde;igus. </eesti>
<inglise>(6) Motor vehicles in category T may also be driven by persons who have the right to drive automobiles in categories C or D or subcategories C1 or D1. </inglise>
<eesti>(7) R-kategooria mootors&otilde;idukit v&otilde;ib juhtida ka isik, kellel on T-kategooria mootors&otilde;iduki juhtimise &otilde;igus v&otilde;i B-, C- v&otilde;i D-kategooria v&otilde;i C1- v&otilde;i D1-alamkategooria auto juhtimise &otilde;igus. </eesti>
<inglise>(7) Motor vehicles in category R may also be driven by persons who have the right to drive motor vehicles in category T or automobiles in categories B, C or D or subcategories C1 or D1. </inglise>
<eesti>&sect; 23. </eesti>
<inglise>&sect; 23. </inglise>
<eesti>Piiratud juhtimis&otilde;igus </eesti>
<inglise>Limited right to drive </inglise>
<eesti>(1) Piiratud juhtimis&otilde;igus on noorema kui k&auml;esoleva seaduse &sect; 29 l&otilde;ikes 1 s&auml;testatud isiku &otilde;igus juhtida mootors&otilde;idukit k&auml;esolevas paragrahvis nimetatud juhtudel ja korras. </eesti>
<inglise>(1) A limited right to drive is the right of persons who are younger than persons provided for in subsection 29 (1) of this Act to drive motor vehicles in the cases and pursuant to the procedure specified in this Act. </inglise>
<eesti>(2) Piiratud juhtimis&otilde;iguse v&otilde;ib B-kategooria auto juhtimiseks anda 16-17-aastasele isikule tingimusel, et mootors&otilde;idukis on tema k&otilde;rval lapsevanem (seaduslik eestkostja) v&otilde;i lapsevanema (seadusliku eestkostja) poolt selleks volitatud isik. </eesti>
<inglise>(2) A limited right to drive automobiles in category B may be granted to a person of 16 to 17 years of age on the condition that his or her parent (legal guardian) or a person authorised by the parent (legal guardian) is next to him or her in the motor vehicle. </inglise>
<eesti>Nimetatud isikutel peab olema B-kategooria auto juhiluba v&auml;hemalt kaks aastat. </eesti>
<inglise>Such person shall have held a category B driving licence for at least two years. </inglise>
<eesti>(3) Piiratud juhtimis&otilde;iguse v&otilde;ib R-kategooria mootors&otilde;iduki juhtimiseks anda v&auml;hemalt 15-aastasele isikule tingimusel, et ta ei vea veoseid teedel ja juhtimine toimub lapsevanema (seadusliku eestkostja) v&otilde;i lapsevanema (seadusliku eestkostja) poolt selleks volitatud isiku vahetu j&auml;relevalve all. </eesti>
<inglise>(3) A limited right to drive motor vehicles in category R may be granted to a person of at least 15 years of age on the condition that he or she does not carry goods on roads and that the driving takes place under the direct supervision of his or her parent (legal guardian) or a person authorised by the parent (legal guardian). </inglise>
<eesti>Nimetatud isikutel peab olema R- v&otilde;i T-kategooria mootors&otilde;iduki juhtimise &otilde;igust t&otilde;endav juhiluba v&auml;hemalt kaks aastat. </eesti>
<inglise>Such person shall have held a driving licence certifying the right to drive motor vehicles in category R or T for at least two years. </inglise>
<eesti>(4) Piiratud juhtimis&otilde;igus annab &otilde;iguse juhtida mootors&otilde;idukit &uuml;ksnes Eestis. </eesti>
<inglise>(4) A limited right to drive grants the right to drive motor vehicles only in Estonia. </inglise>
<eesti>&sect; 24. </eesti>
<inglise>&sect; 24. </inglise>
<eesti>Juhtimis&otilde;igust t&otilde;endav dokument </eesti>
<inglise>Documents certifying right to drive </inglise>
<eesti>(1) Juhtimis&otilde;igust t&otilde;endav dokument on kehtiv juhiluba v&otilde;i seadusega etten&auml;htud juhtudel juhiluba asendav dokument. </eesti>
<inglise>(1) A document certifying the right to drive means a valid driving licence or, in the cases prescribed by law, an equivalent document. </inglise>
<eesti>Igal isikul v&otilde;ib olla ainult &uuml;ks kehtiv juhiluba. </eesti>
<inglise>Any person may hold only one valid driving licence. </inglise>
<eesti>(2) Juhiloa v&otilde;ib &uuml;hitada muu isikut t&otilde;endava dokumendiga. </eesti>
<inglise>(2) A driving licence may be combined with another identity document. </inglise>
<eesti>(3) K&auml;ies juhitava mootors&otilde;iduki juhtimiseks ei ole juhiluba vaja. </eesti>
<inglise>(3) A driving licence is not required to drive a pedestrian controlled motor vehicle. </inglise>
<eesti>(4) Mootors&otilde;idukijuhi koolituskursuse &otilde;pingukaart v&otilde;i tunnistus t&otilde;endab s&otilde;idu&otilde;ppija &otilde;igust juhtida mootors&otilde;idukit &otilde;ppes&otilde;idul k&auml;esoleva seaduse &sect; 32 l&otilde;igetes 1 ja 2 nimetatud tingimustel. </eesti>
<inglise>(4) A learner's form or learner's certificate certifies the right of a learner-driver to drive a motor vehicle during a driving lesson under the conditions specified in subsections 32 (1) and (2) of this Act. </inglise>
<eesti>(5) S&otilde;idueksami kaart t&otilde;endab eksamineeritava &otilde;igust juhtida mootors&otilde;idukit eksamis&otilde;idul. </eesti>
<inglise>(5) A driving test report certifies the right of an examinee to drive a motor vehicle during a driving test. </inglise>
<eesti>(6) K&auml;esoleva seaduse &sect; 30 l&otilde;ike 2 kohaselt vormistatud mootors&otilde;idukijuhi koolituskursuse tunnistus t&otilde;endab juhtimis&otilde;iguse saanud isiku &otilde;igust juhtida mootors&otilde;idukit esmase juhiloa saamiseni. </eesti>
<inglise>(6) A learner's licence prepared according to subsection 30 (2) of this Act certifies that a person who has gained the right to drive has the right to drive a motor vehicle until he or she receives a provisional driving licence. </inglise>
<eesti>(7) Ajutine juhiluba v&auml;ljastatakse isikule, kelle juhtimis&otilde;igus ei ole peatatud, &auml;ra v&otilde;etud v&otilde;i t&uuml;histatud, juhiloa dublikaadi vormistamise ajaks v&otilde;i muul seadusega etten&auml;htud juhul. </eesti>
<inglise>(7) A temporary driving licence shall be issued to a person whose right to drive is not suspended, withdrawn or cancelled for the period when a duplicate driving licence is being prepared or in other cases prescribed by law. </inglise>
<eesti>Ajutine juhiluba kehtib kuni kaks kuud. </eesti>
<inglise>A temporary driving licence is valid for up to two months. </inglise>
<eesti>Ajutine juhiluba annab &otilde;iguse juhtida mootors&otilde;idukit ainult Eestis. </eesti>
<inglise>A temporary driving licence grants the right to drive motor vehicles only in Estonia. </inglise>
<eesti>(8) Juhiloa ja ajutise juhiloa ning k&auml;esoleva seaduse &sect; 30 l&otilde;ikes 2 nimetatud esmase juhiloa liigid ja vormid kehtestab teede- ja sideminister. </eesti>
<inglise>(8) The types and formats of driving licences and temporary driving licences and of provisional driving licences specified in subsection 30 (2) of this Act shall be established by the Minister of Transport and Communications. </inglise>
<eesti>K&otilde;ik nimetatud juhiload peavad vastama Viini 1968. aasta teeliikluse konventsiooni (RT 1992, 12, 194) ning selle juurde kuuluvate hilisemate kokkulepete ja konventsiooni t&auml;ienduste p&otilde;him&otilde;tetele, samuti Euroopa Liidus kehtivatele juhiloa vormin&otilde;uetele. </eesti>
<inglise>All such driving licences shall comply with the principles of the 1968 Vienna Convention on Road Traffic (RT 1992, 12, 194) and subsequent agreements and amendments to the Convention attached thereto, and with the formal requirements for driving licences applicable in the European Union. </inglise>
<eesti>&sect; 25. </eesti>
<inglise>&sect; 25. </inglise>
<eesti>Juhiloa kehtivus </eesti>
<inglise>Terms of driving licences </inglise>
<eesti>(1) Juhiluba kehtib k&uuml;mme aastat, kui k&auml;esoleva seaduse &sect; 28 l&otilde;ike 2 j&auml;rgi kehtestatud n&otilde;uded ei n&auml;e ette l&uuml;hemat t&auml;htaega. </eesti>
<inglise>(1) A driving licence is valid for ten years unless the requirements established according to subsection 28 (2) of this Act prescribe a shorter term. </inglise>
<eesti>(2) Esmane juhiluba kehtib kaks aastat. </eesti>
<inglise>(2) A provisional driving licence is valid for two years. </inglise>
<eesti>&sect; 26. </eesti>
<inglise>&sect; 26. </inglise>
<eesti>Juhiloa v&auml;ljaandmine ja vahetamine </eesti>
<inglise>Issue and replacement of driving licences </inglise>
<eesti>(1) Juhiloa v&auml;ljastab ja vahetab teede- ja sideministri m&auml;&auml;ratud asutus. </eesti>
<inglise>(1) Driving licences shall be issued and replaced by an agency designated by the Minister of Transport and Communications. </inglise>
<eesti>(2) Esmane juhiluba ja juhiluba antakse v&auml;lja 10 t&ouml;&ouml;p&auml;eva jooksul vastava eksami sooritamisele v&otilde;i juhiloa vahetamise taotluse esitamisele j&auml;rgnevast p&auml;evast arvates. </eesti>
<inglise>(2) Provisional driving licences and full driving licences shall be issued within ten working days as of the date on which the corresponding test is passed or an application for replacement of the driving licence is submitted. </inglise>
<eesti>(3) Kui esmase juhiloa taotleja ei ole 12 kuu jooksul, arvates p&auml;evast, mil tekkis esmase juhiloa v&auml;ljaandmise alus, v&otilde;tnud v&auml;lja esmast juhiluba, antakse see v&auml;lja vaid siis, kui isik sooritab edukalt juhtimis&otilde;iguse saamiseks n&otilde;utavad liiklusteooria- ja s&otilde;idueksami. </eesti>
<inglise>(3) If an applicant for a provisional driving licence does not collect his or her provisional driving licence within twelve months as of the date on which the basis for issue of the provisional driving licence arose, the licence shall be issued only if the person passes the theory test and driving test required to obtain the right to drive. </inglise>
<eesti>(4) Kui esmase juhiloa omanik ei ole 12 kuu jooksul, arvates esmase juhiloa kehtivuse m&ouml;&ouml;dumisest, saanud vastava kategooria juhiluba, peab ta uuesti taotlema esmast juhiluba ja sooritama edukalt juhtimis&otilde;iguse saamiseks n&otilde;utavad liiklusteooria- ja s&otilde;idueksami. </eesti>
<inglise>(4) If the holder of a provisional driving licence does not obtain a full driving licence for the corresponding category within twelve months as of the expiry of the provisional driving licence, he or she shall re-apply for a provisional driving licence and retake the theory test and driving test required to obtain the right to drive. </inglise>
<eesti>&sect; 27. </eesti>
<inglise>&sect; 27. </inglise>
<eesti>V&auml;lisriigis v&auml;ljaantud juhiluba </eesti>
<inglise>Driving licences issued in foreign states </inglise>
<eesti>(1) Eestis kehtib v&auml;lisriigis v&auml;ljaantud juhiluba, mis on v&auml;lja antud ja vormistatud vastavalt Viini 1968. aasta teeliikluse konventsiooni ning selle juurde kuuluvate hilisemate kokkulepete ja konventsiooni t&auml;ienduste p&otilde;him&otilde;tetele. </eesti>
<inglise>(1) A driving licence issued in a foreign state is valid in Estonia if it is issued and prepared pursuant to the principles of the 1968 Vienna Convention on Road Traffic and subsequent agreements and amendments to the Convention attached thereto. </inglise>
<eesti>(2) Eestisse elama asunud isiku v&auml;lisriigis v&auml;ljaantud juhiluba kehtib Eestis &uuml;ks aasta juhiloa omaniku Eestisse saabumisest arvates. </eesti>
<inglise>(2) A driving licence which is issued in a foreign state and which is held by a person who has settled in Estonia is valid in Estonia for one year after the holder of the driving licence arrives in Estonia. </inglise>
<eesti>V&auml;lisriigis v&auml;ljaantud juhiloa vahetamiseks Eesti juhiloa vastu peab taotleja edukalt sooritama liiklusteooria- ja s&otilde;idueksami. </eesti>
<inglise>In order to replace a driving licence issued in a foreign state with an Estonian driving licence, the applicant shall pass the theory test and the driving test. </inglise>
<eesti>6. peat&uuml;kk </eesti>
<inglise>Chapter 6 </inglise>
<eesti>Mootors&otilde;iduki juhtimise &otilde;iguse andmine </eesti>
<inglise>Grant of Right to Drive Motor Vehicles </inglise>
<eesti>&sect; 28. </eesti>
<inglise>&sect; 28. </inglise>
<eesti>Juhtimis&otilde;iguse andmise tingimused </eesti>
<inglise>Conditions for grant of right to drive </inglise>
<eesti>(1) Juhtimis&otilde;igus antakse Eesti kodanikule, kelle alaline elukoht on Eestis, ja elamisloa alusel Eestis viibivale v&auml;lismaalasele, kui nende vanus ja terviseseisund vastavad kehtivatele n&otilde;uetele ja kui nad on saanud vastava ettevalmistuse ning edukalt sooritanud n&otilde;utavad liiklusteooria- ja s&otilde;idueksami. </eesti>
<inglise>(1) The right to drive shall be granted to Estonian citizens who reside permanently in Estonia and to aliens staying in Estonia on the basis of residence permits if their age and state of health meet the requirements in force and if they have received the appropriate training and passed the required theory test and driving test. </inglise>
<eesti>(2) N&otilde;uded mootors&otilde;idukijuhi terviseseisundile, kutsesobivusele ja esmaabialasele v&auml;lja&otilde;ppele kehtestab sotsiaalminister. </eesti>
<inglise>(2) The requirements for the state of health, professional suitability and first aid training of motor vehicle drivers shall be established by the Minister of Social Affairs. </inglise>
<eesti>(3) Mootors&otilde;idukijuhi teadmiste, oskuste ja k&auml;itumise liiklusalased kvalifikatsioonin&otilde;uded kehtestab teede- ja sideminister, arvestades, et juht peab tundma liiklusalaste &otilde;igusaktide n&otilde;udeid ning oskama valitseda s&otilde;idukit, j&auml;lgida liiklust, m&auml;rgata ja ette n&auml;ha v&otilde;imalikke ohte ning sellele vastavalt tegutseda. </eesti>
<inglise>(3) The requirements for the knowledge, skills and behaviour of drivers of motor vehicles shall be established by the Minister of Transport and Communications, taking into account the fact that drivers must be familiar with the requirements of legislation concerning traffic and be able to control a vehicle, appreciate traffic environment, be aware of and foresee possible hazards and act accordingly. </inglise>
<eesti>(4) Mootors&otilde;idukijuhi ettevalmistamise, eksamineerimise ning talle juhtimis&otilde;iguse andmise eeskirjad ja riiklikud &otilde;ppekavad kehtestab teede- ja sideminister. </eesti>
<inglise>(4) The rules for the training and testing of and for the grant of the right to drive to drivers of motor vehicles, and the national training plans for drivers of motor vehicles shall be established by the Minister of Transport and Communications. </inglise>
<eesti>&sect; 29. </eesti>
<inglise>&sect; 29. </inglise>
<eesti>Juhi vanuse alamm&auml;&auml;r </eesti>
<inglise>Minimum age of drivers </inglise>
<eesti>(1) Olenevalt mootors&otilde;iduki kategooriast v&otilde;ib (v&auml;lja arvatud k&auml;esoleva seaduse &sect;-s 23 s&auml;testatud piiratud juhtimis&otilde;iguse juhtudel) juhtimis&otilde;iguse anda isikule, kes on v&auml;hemalt: </eesti>
<inglise>(1) Depending on the category of motor vehicle, (except in cases of limited rights to drive provided for in &sect; 23 of this Act), the right to drive may be granted to persons who are at least: </inglise>
<eesti>1) 16-aastane - A1-alamkategooria mootorratas, B1-alamkategooria auto, R-kategooria mootors&otilde;iduk; </eesti>
<inglise>1) 16 years of age - motorcycles in subcategory A1, automobiles in subcategory B1, motor vehicles in category R; </inglise>
<eesti>2) 18-aastane - A-kategooria mootorratas, mille mootori v&otilde;imsus ei &uuml;leta 25 kW v&otilde;i eriv&otilde;imsus ei &uuml;leta 0,16 kW/kg, B-kategooria auto, C1-alamkategooria auto, T-kategooria mootors&otilde;iduk; </eesti>
<inglise>2) 18 years of age - motorcycles in category A with engine power not exceeding 25 kW or effective engine power not exceeding 0.16 kW/kg, automobiles in category B, automobiles in subcategory C1, motor vehicles in category T; </inglise>
<eesti>3) 21-aastane - A-kategooria mootorratas, mille mootori v&otilde;imsus &uuml;letab 25 kW v&otilde;i eriv&otilde;imsus &uuml;letab 0,16 kW/kg; C-, D-kategooria ja D1-alamkategooria auto. </eesti>
<inglise>3) 21 years of age - motorcycles in category A with engine power exceeding 25 kW or effective engine power exceeding 0.16 kW/kg, automobiles in categories C and D and subcategory D1. </inglise>
<eesti>(2) K&auml;esoleva seaduse &sect; 32 l&otilde;igetes 1 ja 2 nimetatud &otilde;ppes&otilde;it v&otilde;i s&otilde;idupraktika on lubatud B-kategooria ja B1-alamkategooria autoga, A1-alamkategooria mootorrattaga ja R-kategooria mootors&otilde;idukiga alates 15,5 -aastaselt ning C1-alamkategooria autoga alates 17-aastaselt. </eesti>
<inglise>(2) Driving lessons or driving practice specified in subsections 32 (1) and (2) of this Act is permitted using automobiles in category B and subcategory B1, motorcycles in subcategory A1 and motor vehicles in category R from 15.5 years of age, and using automobiles in subcategory C1 from 17 years of age. </inglise>
<eesti>(3) C-, D-kategooria auto ja CE-kategooria autorongi juhtimise &otilde;iguse v&otilde;ib anda v&auml;hemalt 18-aastasele kaitseteenistuse ajateenijale &uuml;ksnes teenistus&uuml;lesannete t&auml;itmiseks. </eesti>
<inglise>(3) The right to drive automobiles in categories C and D and road trains in category CE may be granted to conscripts, who are of at least 18 years of age who are serving in the defence service, only for the performance of their duties. </inglise>
<eesti>&sect; 30. </eesti>
<inglise>&sect; 30. </inglise>
<eesti>Auto ja mootorratta juhtimise &otilde;iguse andmise etapid </eesti>
<inglise>Stages in grant of right to drive automobiles and motorcycles </inglise>
<eesti>(1) A-kategooria ja A1-alamkategooria mootorratta, v&auml;lja arvatud A-kategooria mootorratas, mille mootori v&otilde;imsus &uuml;letab 25 kW v&otilde;i eriv&otilde;imsus &uuml;letab 0,16 kW/kg, B-kategooria auto ja B1-alamkategooria auto v&otilde;i &uuml;heaegselt B- ja C1-kategooria auto juhtimise &otilde;iguse andmine toimub kahes etapis k&auml;esoleva seaduse &sect; 28 l&otilde;ike 4 kohaselt kehtestatud eeskirjade j&auml;rgi. </eesti>
<inglise>(1) The right to drive motorcycles in category A and subcategory A1, except motorcycles in category A with engine power exceeding 25 kW or effective engine power exceeding 0.16 kW/kg, automobiles in category B and automobiles in subcategory B1 or automobiles in both category B and category C1 shall be granted in two stages according to the rules established pursuant to subsection 28 (4) of this Act. </inglise>
<eesti>(2) Isikule, kellel varem ei ole olnud auto v&otilde;i mootorratta juhtimise &otilde;igust, antakse esimeses etapis k&auml;esoleva paragrahvi l&otilde;ikes 1 nimetatud mootors&otilde;idukite juhtimiseks esmane juhiluba k&auml;esoleva seaduse &sect; 28 l&otilde;ike 4 kohaselt kehtestatud eeskirjade j&auml;rgi. </eesti>
<inglise>(2) In the first stage, provisional driving licences to drive the motor vehicles specified in subsection (1) of this section shall be issued to persons who previously did not have the right to drive automobiles or motorcycles according to the rules established pursuant to subsection 28 (4) of this Act. </inglise>
<eesti>P&auml;rast eksamitulemuste vormistamist ja kuni esmase juhiloa saamiseni, kuid mitte kauem kui 15 p&auml;eva eksami sooritamisest arvates, t&otilde;endab juhtimis&otilde;iguse saanud isiku &otilde;igust juhtida mootors&otilde;idukit iseseisvalt mootors&otilde;idukijuhi koolituskursuse tunnistus, millele teede- ja sideministri m&auml;&auml;ratud asutus on teinud kande juhtimis&otilde;iguse andmise kohta. </eesti>
<inglise>After the test results are officially registered and until a provisional driving licence is obtained, but for not longer than fifteen days as of passing the test, a learner's certificate, on which an agency designated by the Minister of Transport and Communications has made an entry concerning the grant of the right to drive, certifies that a person who has gained the right to drive has the right to drive a motor vehicle independently. </inglise>
<eesti>Nimetatud tunnistus annab &otilde;iguse juhtida mootors&otilde;idukit &uuml;ksnes Eestis. </eesti>
<inglise>Such learner's licence grants the right to drive motor vehicles only in Estonia. </inglise>
<eesti>(3) Kui esmase juhiloa omanik on omandanud vajaliku vilumuse ja l&auml;binud l&otilde;ppastme koolituse, antakse talle k&auml;esoleva seaduse &sect; 28 l&otilde;ike 4 kohaselt kehtestatud eeskirjade j&auml;rgi juhiluba. </eesti>
<inglise>(3) When the holder of a provisional driving licence has acquired the necessary experience and undergone final stage training, a driving licence shall be issued to him or her according to the rules established pursuant to subsection 28 (4) of this Act. </inglise>
<eesti>(4) Kui esmase juhiloa omanikku on haldus- v&otilde;i kriminaalkorras karistatud selliste liiklusalaste n&otilde;uete rikkumise eest, mille eest on karistusena ette n&auml;htud juhtimis&otilde;iguse &auml;rav&otilde;tmine, t&uuml;histatakse juhtimis&otilde;igus. </eesti>
<inglise>(4) If the holder of a provisional driving licence has been punished pursuant to administrative or criminal procedure for violating traffic requirements and if the punishment prescribed therefor is withdrawal of the right to drive, his or her right to drive shall be cancelled. </inglise>
<eesti>(5) Kui esmase juhiloa omanikku on viimase 12 kuu jooksul halduskorras karistatud selliste liiklusalaste n&otilde;uete rikkumise eest, mille eest ei ole karistusena ette n&auml;htud juhtimis&otilde;iguse &auml;rav&otilde;tmist, antakse talle k&auml;esoleva paragrahvi l&otilde;ike 3 tingimuste t&auml;itmise korral juhiluba p&auml;rast liiklusteooria- ja s&otilde;idueksami edukat sooritamist. </eesti>
<inglise>(5) If the holder of a provisional driving licence has been punished pursuant to administrative procedure within the last twelve months for violating traffic requirements and if the punishment prescribed therefor does not include withdrawal of the right to drive, a driving licence shall be issued to him or her after he or she has passed the theory test and driving test and if he or she meets the conditions of subsection (3) of this section. </inglise>
<eesti>&sect; 31. </eesti>
<inglise>&sect; 31. </inglise>
<eesti>C- ja D-kategooria ning C1- ja D1-alamkategooria auto ning autorongi juhtimise &otilde;iguse andmine </eesti>
<inglise>Grant of right to drive category C and D and subcategory C1 and D1 automobiles, and road trains </inglise>
<eesti>(1) C-kategooria ja D1-alamkategooria auto juhtimise &otilde;iguse v&otilde;ib anda isikule, kellel on B-kategooria auto juhiluba v&auml;hemalt &uuml;ks aasta. </eesti>
<inglise>(1) The right to drive automobiles in category C and subcategory D1 may be granted to a person who has held a category B driving licence for at least one year. </inglise>
<eesti>(2) D-kategooria auto juhtimise &otilde;iguse v&otilde;ib anda isikule, kellel on B-kategooria auto juhiluba v&auml;hemalt kaks aastat. </eesti>
<inglise>(2) The right to drive automobiles in category D may be granted to a person who has held a category B driving licence for at least two years. </inglise>
<eesti>(3) C1-alamkategooria auto juhtimise &otilde;iguse v&otilde;ib anda isikule koos B-kategooria auto juhtimise &otilde;iguse andmisega v&otilde;i isikule, kellel on B-kategooria auto juhtimise &otilde;igus. </eesti>
<inglise>(3) The right to drive automobiles in subcategory C1 may be granted to a person at the same time as he or she is granted the right to drive automobiles in category B or to a person who has been granted the right to drive automobiles in category B. </inglise>
<eesti>(4) BE-, CE- v&otilde;i DE-kategooria ja C1E- v&otilde;i D1E-alamkategooria autorongi juhtimise &otilde;iguse v&otilde;ib anda isikule, kellel on vastava kategooria vedukauto juhtimise &otilde;igus. </eesti>
<inglise>(4) The right to drive road trains in categories BE, CE or DE and subcategories C1E or D1E may be granted to a person who has been granted the right to drive the corresponding category of lorry or truck. </inglise>
<eesti>(5) K&auml;esolevas paragrahvis loetletud autode ja autorongide kategooriate juhtimise &otilde;igus antakse isikule p&auml;rast vastavat ettevalmistust ning liiklusteooria- ja s&otilde;idueksami edukat sooritamist k&auml;esoleva seaduse &sect; 28 l&otilde;ike 4 kohaselt kehtestatud eeskirjade j&auml;rgi. </eesti>
<inglise>(5) The right to drive automobiles and road trains in the categories listed in this section shall be granted to a person after he or she has undergone the corresponding training and passed the theory test and driving test according to the rules established pursuant to subsection 28 (4) of this Act. </inglise>
<eesti>(6) K&auml;esolevas paragrahvis loetletud autode ja autorongide kategooriate juhtimise &otilde;igust ei v&otilde;i anda isikule, kellel on k&auml;esoleva seaduse &sect;-s 30 nimetatud esmane juhiluba. </eesti>
<inglise>(6) The right to drive automobiles and road trains in the categories listed in this section shall not be granted to a person who holds a provisional driving licence specified in &sect; 30 of this Act. </inglise>
<eesti>&sect; 32. </eesti>
<inglise>&sect; 32. </inglise>
<eesti>Mootors&otilde;iduki juhtimine &otilde;ppes&otilde;idul </eesti>
<inglise>Driving motor vehicles during driving lessons </inglise>
<eesti>(1) Isik, kes &otilde;pib mootors&otilde;idukijuhi koolituskursusel, v&otilde;ib juhtida mootors&otilde;idukit &otilde;ppes&otilde;idu ajal mootors&otilde;idukijuhi &otilde;petaja juuresolekul. </eesti>
<inglise>(1) A person who takes a training course for drivers of motor vehicles may drive a motor vehicle during driving lessons in the presence of a driving instructor. </inglise>
<eesti>(2) Isik, kes &otilde;pib mootors&otilde;idukijuhi koolituskursusel v&otilde;i on koolituskursuse l&otilde;petanud, v&otilde;ib juhtida mootors&otilde;idukit s&otilde;idupraktika saamise eesm&auml;rgil ka teise isiku (edaspidi juhendaja) juuresolekul j&auml;rgmistel tingimustel: </eesti>
<inglise>(2) In order to gain driving experience, a person who takes or has taken a training course for drivers of motor vehicles may drive a motor vehicle in the presence of another person (hereinafter instructor) provided that the following conditions are met: </inglise>
<eesti>1) juhendajal peab olema vastava kategooria mootors&otilde;iduki juhiluba v&auml;hemalt viis aastat; </eesti>
<inglise>1) the instructor has held a driving licence for the corresponding category of motor vehicle for at least five years; </inglise>
<eesti>2) juhendajat ei ole karistatud viimase viie aasta jooksul mootors&otilde;iduki joobes juhtimise eest ega viimase kolme aasta jooksul liiklusalaste &otilde;igusaktide n&otilde;uete sellise rikkumise eest, mille eest on ette n&auml;htud mootors&otilde;iduki juhtimise &otilde;iguse &auml;rav&otilde;tmine; </eesti>
<inglise>2) the instructor has not been punished within the last five years for driving a motor vehicle while intoxicated or within the last three years for violating requirements of legislation concerning traffic for which the prescribed punishment is withdrawal of the right to drive; </inglise>
<eesti>3) juhendaja on saanud teede- ja sideministri m&auml;&auml;ratud asutuselt tunnistuse selle kohta, et ta vastab k&auml;esoleva l&otilde;ike punktides 1 ja 2 nimetatud tingimustele. </eesti>
<inglise>3) the instructor has obtained a certificate from the agency designated by the Minister of Transport and Communications certifying that he or she meets the requirements specified in clauses 1) and 2) of this subsection. </inglise>
<eesti>Tunnistuse vormi ja v&auml;ljaandmise korra kehtestab teede- ja sideminister. </eesti>
<inglise>The format of and procedure for issue of such certificates shall be established by the Minister of Transport and Communications. </inglise>
<eesti>(3) K&auml;esoleva paragrahvi l&otilde;ikes 1 nimetatud mootors&otilde;idukijuhi &otilde;petaja ja l&otilde;ikes 2 nimetatud juhendaja loetakse &otilde;ppes&otilde;idu ja s&otilde;idupraktika ajal juhiks. </eesti>
<inglise>(3) Driving instructors specified in subsection (1) and instructors specified in subsection (2) of this section are deemed to be drivers during driving lessons and driving practice. </inglise>
<eesti>(4) Kui k&auml;esoleva paragrahvi l&otilde;ikes 2 nimetatud s&otilde;idu&otilde;ppija on noorem kui 18-aastane, v&otilde;ib juhendajaks olla &uuml;ksnes tema vanem v&otilde;i seaduslik eestkostja. </eesti>
<inglise>(4) If a learner-driver specified in subsection (2) of this section is younger than 18 years of age, only his or her parent or legal guardian may be the instructor. </inglise>
<eesti>&sect; 33. </eesti>
<inglise>&sect; 33. </inglise>
<eesti>Mootors&otilde;iduki juhtimine eksamis&otilde;idul </eesti>
<inglise>Driving motor vehicle during driving test </inglise>
<eesti>(1) Mootors&otilde;iduki juhtimise aluseks eksamis&otilde;idul on teede- ja sideministri m&auml;&auml;ratud asutuse poolt eksamineeritava nimele vormistatud s&otilde;idueksami kaart. </eesti>
<inglise>(1) The document which is the basis for driving a motor vehicle during a driving test is the driving test report prepared in the name of the examinee by the agency designated by the Minister of Transport and Communications. </inglise>
<eesti>(2) K&auml;esoleva paragrahvi l&otilde;ikes 1 nimetatud s&otilde;idueksami kaart vormistatakse p&auml;rast liiklusteooriaeksami sooritamist. </eesti>
<inglise>(2) A driving test report specified in subsection (1) of this section shall be prepared after the theory test is passed. </inglise>
<eesti>(3) K&auml;esoleva paragrahvi l&otilde;ikes 1 nimetatud eksamineeritav loetakse juhiks. </eesti>
<inglise>(3) An examinee specified in subsection (1) of this section is deemed to be a driver. </inglise>
<eesti>(4) Esmase juhiloa taotleja ei v&otilde;i sooritada s&otilde;idueksamit varem kui kolm kuud enne k&auml;esoleva seaduse &sect; 29 l&otilde;ikes 1 nimetatud vanuseni j&otilde;udmist. </eesti>
<inglise>(4) An applicant for a provisional driving licence shall not take a driving test earlier than three months before attaining the age specified in subsection 29 (1) of this Act. </inglise>
<eesti>7. peat&uuml;kk </eesti>
<inglise>Chapter 7 </inglise>
<eesti>Mootors&otilde;idukijuhi koolitus </eesti>
<inglise>Training of Drivers of Motor Vehicles </inglise>
<eesti>&sect; 34. </eesti>
<inglise>&sect; 34. </inglise>
<eesti>Mootors&otilde;idukijuhi koolitaja </eesti>
<inglise>Providers of training for drivers of motor vehicles </inglise>
<eesti>(1) Mootors&otilde;idukijuhi koolitust teostavad era&otilde;iguslikud juriidilised isikud, f&uuml;&uuml;silisest isikust ettev&otilde;tjad ning riigi- ja munitsipaalharidusasutused, kes on kantud &auml;riregistrisse v&otilde;i seaduse alusel teise registrisse ja kellel on mootors&otilde;idukijuhi koolitamise luba (edaspidi koolitusluba). </eesti>
<inglise>(1) Training for drivers of motor vehicles shall be provided by legal persons in private law, sole proprietors and state and municipal educational institutions which are entered in the commercial register or, pursuant to law, another register and which hold a licence to provide training for drivers of motor vehicles (hereinafter education licence). </inglise>
<eesti>(2) Koolitusloa annab haridusminister kolmeks aastaks, kui loa taotleja ei soovi seda l&uuml;hemaks ajaks. </eesti>
<inglise>(2) The Minister of Education shall issue an education licence for three years unless the applicant requests a shorter period. </inglise>
<eesti>Koolitusluba antakse, s&otilde;ltumata koolituse &uuml;he kursuse &otilde;ppetundide mahust. </eesti>
<inglise>An education licence shall be issued regardless of the number of lessons in one training course. </inglise>
<eesti>(3) Koolitusloa v&auml;ljastamise ja kehtetuks tunnistamise korra kehtestab haridusminister. </eesti>
<inglise>(3) The procedure for the issue and revocation of education licences shall be established by the Minister of Education. </inglise>
<eesti>&sect; 35. </eesti>
<inglise>&sect; 35. </inglise>
<eesti>Mootors&otilde;idukijuhi koolitajale esitatavad n&otilde;uded </eesti>
<inglise>Requirements for providers of training for drivers of motor vehicles </inglise>
<eesti>Mootors&otilde;idukijuhi koolitajal (edaspidi koolitaja) peavad olema: </eesti>
<inglise>A provider of training for drivers of motor vehicles (hereinafter training provider) shall have: </inglise>
<eesti>1) tervisekaitsen&otilde;uetele vastavad &otilde;pperuumid (hooned, sisustus ja muu vara) v&otilde;i nende kasutamise v&otilde;imalus; </eesti>
<inglise>1) study rooms (buildings, furnishings and other property) which comply with the health protection requirements or the possibility to use such rooms; </inglise>
<eesti>2) &otilde;ppes&otilde;iduv&auml;ljak v&otilde;i selle kasutamise v&otilde;imalus; </eesti>
<inglise>2) a practice area or the possibility to use a practice area; </inglise>
<eesti>3) &otilde;igusaktides s&auml;testatud n&otilde;uetele vastavad &otilde;ppes&otilde;idukid v&otilde;i &otilde;ppes&otilde;idukite kasutamise v&otilde;imalus; </eesti>
<inglise>3) vehicles for driving practice which comply with the requirements provided by legislation or the possibility to use such vehicles; </inglise>
<eesti>4) k&auml;esoleva seaduse &sect; 36 l&otilde;ike 2 kohaselt kehtestatud eeskirjale vastavad &otilde;petajad; </eesti>
<inglise>4) instructors who comply with the rules established pursuant to subsection 36 (2) of this Act; </inglise>
<eesti>5) k&auml;esoleva seaduse &sect; 28 l&otilde;ike 4 kohaselt kehtestatud eeskirjadele vastavad &otilde;ppekavad ja &otilde;ppedokumentatsioon; </eesti>
<inglise>5) training plans and training documentation which comply with the rules established pursuant to subsection 28 (4) of this Act; </inglise>
<eesti>6) &otilde;ppekavades etten&auml;htud metoodilised ja audiovisuaalsed &otilde;ppevahendid ning tarvikud. </eesti>
<inglise>6) the methodological and audiovisual teaching aids and accessories which are prescribed in the training plans. </inglise>
<eesti>&sect; 36. </eesti>
<inglise>&sect; 36. </inglise>
<eesti>Mootors&otilde;idukijuhi &otilde;petajale esitatavad n&otilde;uded </eesti>
<inglise>Requirements for driving instructors </inglise>
<eesti>(1) Mootors&otilde;idukijuhi &otilde;petaja kvalifikatsiooni v&otilde;ib taotleda v&auml;hemalt 21-aastane isik, kellel on &otilde;petatava kategooria mootors&otilde;iduki juhtimise &otilde;igust t&otilde;endav juhiluba v&auml;hemalt kolm aastat ja keda ei ole karistatud viimase viie aasta jooksul mootors&otilde;iduki joobes juhtimise eest ega viimase kolme aasta jooksul liiklusalaste &otilde;igusaktide n&otilde;uete sellise rikkumise eest, mille eest on ette n&auml;htud mootors&otilde;iduki juhtimise &otilde;iguse &auml;rav&otilde;tmine. </eesti>
<inglise>(1) A person who is of at least 21 years of age, who has held a driving licence certifying the right to drive motor vehicles in the category to be taught for at least three years and who has not been punished within the last five years for driving a motor vehicle while intoxicated or within the last three years for violating requirements of legislation concerning traffic for which the prescribed punishment is withdrawal of the right to drive may apply for the qualification of driving instructor. </inglise>
<eesti>(2) N&otilde;uded mootors&otilde;idukijuhi &otilde;petaja kvalifikatsioonile, riikliku &otilde;ppekava ning &otilde;petajale koolitamise &otilde;igust t&otilde;endava tunnistuse andmise ja kehtetuks tunnistamise eeskirja kehtestab teede- ja sideminister. </eesti>
<inglise>(2) The requirements for the qualifications of driving instructors, the national training plan and the rules for the issue to instructors of certificates attesting their right to teach and for the revocation thereof shall be established by the Minister of Transport and Communications. </inglise>
<eesti>(3) Mootors&otilde;idukijuhi &otilde;petaja tunnistuse v&auml;ljastab teede- ja sideministri m&auml;&auml;ratud asutus. </eesti>
<inglise>(3) Driving instructor certificates shall be issued by the agency designated by the Minister of Transport and Communications. </inglise>
<eesti>(4) Mootors&otilde;idukijuhi &otilde;petajalt v&otilde;etakse koolitamise &otilde;igus &auml;ra, kui teda on karistatud liiklusohu v&otilde;i liiklus&otilde;nnetuse tekitamise eest v&otilde;i k&auml;esoleva paragrahvi l&otilde;ikes 1 nimetatud rikkumiste eest v&otilde;i kui ta on sooritanud sellise rikkumise, mis paneb kahtluse alla tema sobivuse mootors&otilde;idukijuhi &otilde;petajana t&ouml;&ouml;tamiseks. </eesti>
<inglise>(4) A driving instructor shall be deprived of the right to teach if he or she has been punished for causing a traffic hazard or traffic accident or for a violation specified in subsection (1) of this section or if he or she has committed a violation which calls into question his or her suitability to work as a driving instructor. </inglise>
<eesti>&sect; 37. </eesti>
<inglise>&sect; 37. </inglise>
<eesti>Koolitusloa taotlemine ja taotluse l&auml;bivaatamine </eesti>
<inglise>Application for education licence and review of applications </inglise>
<eesti>(1) Koolitusloa saamiseks esitab taotleja loa andjale j&auml;rgmised dokumendid: </eesti>
<inglise>(1) In order to obtain an education licence, an applicant shall submit the following documents to the agency which issues licences: </inglise>
<eesti>1) koolitusloa taotlus; </eesti>
<inglise>1) an application for an education licence; </inglise>
<eesti>2) &auml;riregistrisse kantud ettev&otilde;tja puhul registrikaardi &auml;rakiri ja seaduse alusel teise registrisse kantud isiku puhul v&auml;ljav&otilde;te sellest registrist; </eesti>
<inglise>2) in the case of an undertaking entered in the commercial register, a copy of the registry card, and in the case of a person entered in another register pursuant to law, an extract from the register; </inglise>
<eesti>3) p&otilde;hikiri v&otilde;i &uuml;hinguleping (v&auml;lja arvatud f&uuml;&uuml;silisest isikust ettev&otilde;tja puhul); </eesti>
<inglise>3) the articles of association or partnership agreement (except in the case of a sole proprietor); </inglise>
<eesti>4) k&auml;esoleva seaduse &sect; 35 punktides 1-3 s&auml;testatud ruumide, &otilde;ppes&otilde;iduv&auml;ljaku ja &otilde;ppes&otilde;idukite olemasolu v&otilde;i rentimist t&otilde;endavad dokumendid, punktides 5 ja 6 s&auml;testatud &otilde;ppekava, &otilde;ppedokumentatsioon ja audiovisuaalsete &otilde;ppevahendite loetelu ning teede- ja sideministri volitatud asutuse kirjalik hinnang nende vastavuse kohta k&auml;esolevas seaduses s&auml;testatud n&otilde;uetele; </eesti>
<inglise>4) documents certifying the existence or rental of the rooms, practice area and vehicles for driving practice provided for in clauses 35 1) -3) of this Act, the training plan, the training documentation and a list of the methodological and audiovisual teaching aids provided for in clauses 35 5) and 6), and a written assessment from the agency authorised by the Minister of Transport and Communications concerning the compliance thereof with the requirements provided for in this Act; </inglise>
<eesti>5) &otilde;petajate kirjalikud n&otilde;usolekud t&ouml;&ouml;le asumiseks; </eesti>
<inglise>5) written consent from the instructors to commence work; </inglise>
<eesti>6) Maksuameti kohaliku asutuse t&otilde;end maksuv&otilde;lgnevuse puudumise kohta; </eesti>
<inglise>6) a statement from the local Tax Board Office certifying the absence of tax arrears; </inglise>
<eesti>7) koolitusloa eest riigil&otilde;ivu tasumist t&otilde;endav dokument. </eesti>
<inglise>7) a document certifying payment of the state fee for an education licence. </inglise>
<eesti>(2) Koolitusloa andja annab koolitusloa v&otilde;i teatab loa taotlejale koolitusloa andmisest keeldumisest kirjalikult 30 kalendrip&auml;eva jooksul k&auml;esoleva paragrahvi l&otilde;ikes 1 nimetatud dokumentide esitamisest arvates. </eesti>
<inglise>(2) An agency which issues education licences shall issue an education licence or inform the applicant for the licence in writing of the refusal to issue an education licence within thirty calendar days as of the submission of the documents specified in subsection (1) of this section. </inglise>
<eesti>(3) Koolitusloa andja keeldub koolitusloa andmisest, kui taotleja ei vasta k&auml;esoleva seaduse &sect;-s 35 nimetatud n&otilde;uetele v&otilde;i on maksuv&otilde;lglane. </eesti>
<inglise>(3) An agency which issues education licences shall refuse to issue an education licence if the applicant does not meet the requirements specified in &sect; 35 of this Act or owes arrears. </inglise>
<eesti>&sect; 38. </eesti>
<inglise>&sect; 38. </inglise>
<eesti>Riiklik j&auml;relevalve mootors&otilde;idukijuhi koolituse &uuml;le </eesti>
<inglise>State supervision over training of drivers of motor vehicles </inglise>
<eesti>(1) Riiklikku j&auml;relevalvet mootors&otilde;idukijuhi koolituse &uuml;le teostavad haridusministri ning teede- ja sideministri volitatud asutused. </eesti>
<inglise>(1) State supervision over the training of drivers of motor vehicles shall be exercised by agencies authorised by the Minister of Education and the Minister of Transport and Communications. </inglise>
<eesti>(2) Kui mootors&otilde;idukijuhi koolitus ei vasta k&auml;esolevas seaduses v&otilde;i selle alusel antud &otilde;igusaktides s&auml;testatud n&otilde;uetele, on riiklikku j&auml;relevalvet teostaval asutusel &otilde;igus teha koolitajale ettekirjutus puuduste k&otilde;rvaldamiseks ning &otilde;ppetegevuse parandamiseks. </eesti>
<inglise>(2) If training provided for drivers of motor vehicles does not comply with the requirements provided for in this Act or legislation issued on the basis thereof, an agency which exercises state supervision has the right to issue a precept to the training provider for the elimination of the deficiencies and an improvement in the provision of education. </inglise>
<eesti>Koolitaja on kohustatud ettekirjutuse t&auml;itma selles s&auml;testatud t&auml;htaja jooksul. </eesti>
<inglise>The training provider is required to comply with the precept within the term provided for therein. </inglise>
<eesti>&sect; 39. </eesti>
<inglise>&sect; 39. </inglise>
<eesti>Koolitusloa kehtetuks tunnistamine </eesti>
<inglise>Revocation of education licence </inglise>
<eesti>(1) Koolitusluba tunnistatakse kehtetuks, kui: </eesti>
<inglise>(1) An education licence shall be revoked if: </inglise>
<eesti>1) selgub, et koolitusloa taotlemisel on esitatud valeandmeid; </eesti>
<inglise>1) it becomes evident that false information was submitted upon application for the education licence; </inglise>
<eesti>2) koolitaja ei ole m&auml;&auml;ratud t&auml;htajaks ja korras t&auml;itnud vastava j&auml;relevalveasutuse poolt temale tehtud ettekirjutust; </eesti>
<inglise>2) the training provider fails to comply with a precept issued thereto by a corresponding supervisory agency by the date and pursuant to the procedure specified; </inglise>
<eesti>3) koolitaja on teinud otsuse mootors&otilde;idukijuhi koolituse l&otilde;petamise kohta; </eesti>
<inglise>3) the training provider decides to terminate the provision of training for drivers of motor vehicles; </inglise>
<eesti>4) koolitaja vastu on algatatud likvideerimismenetlus; </eesti>
<inglise>4) liquidation proceedings have been commenced against the training provider; </inglise>
<eesti>5) mootors&otilde;idukijuhi koolitus ei vasta k&auml;esoleva seaduse v&otilde;i selle alusel antud &otilde;igusaktides s&auml;testatud n&otilde;uetele; </eesti>
<inglise>5) the training provided for drivers of motor vehicles does not comply with the requirements provided for in this Act or legislation issued on the basis thereof; </inglise>
<eesti>6) koolitaja ei ole &uuml;he aasta jooksul koolitusloa kehtivuse algusest arvates tegevust alustanud v&otilde;i ei ole viimase aasta jooksul &otilde;ppet&ouml;&ouml;d teostanud. </eesti>
<inglise>6) the training provider has not commenced providing training within one year after the beginning of the validity of the education licence or has not provided training within the last year. </inglise>
<eesti>(2) Koolitusloa andja teavitab koolitajat talle antud koolitusloa kehtetuks tunnistamisest 10 t&ouml;&ouml;p&auml;eva jooksul vastava otsuse tegemisest arvates. </eesti>
<inglise>(2) The agency which issued the education licence shall notify the training provider of the revocation of the education licence issued thereto within ten working days as of the corresponding decision being made. </inglise>
<eesti>&sect; 40. </eesti>
<inglise>&sect; 40. </inglise>
<eesti>Mootors&otilde;idukijuhi ettevalmistamine &uuml;ksikkorras </eesti>
<inglise>Training of drivers of motor vehicles on individual basis </inglise>
<eesti>&Uuml;ksikkorras v&otilde;ib mootors&otilde;idukijuhti ette valmistada k&auml;esoleva seaduse &sect;-s 34 nimetatud koolitaja juhendamisel k&auml;esoleva seaduse &sect; 28 l&otilde;ike 4 kohaselt kehtestatud eeskirja j&auml;rgi. </eesti>
<inglise>Drivers of motor vehicles may be trained on an individual basis under the supervision of a training provider specified in &sect; 34 of this Act according to the rules established pursuant to subsection 28 (4) of this Act. </inglise>
<eesti>8. peat&uuml;kk </eesti>
<inglise>Chapter 8 </inglise>
<eesti>Mootors&otilde;iduki juhtimise &otilde;iguse peatamine, &auml;rav&otilde;tmine, t&uuml;histamine ja taastamine </eesti>
<inglise>Suspension, Withdrawal, Cancellation and Restoration of Right to Drive </inglise>
<eesti>&sect; 41. </eesti>
<inglise>&sect; 41. </inglise>
<eesti>Juhtimis&otilde;iguse peatamine </eesti>
<inglise>Suspension of right to drive </inglise>
<eesti>(1) Juhtimis&otilde;iguse peatamine on isikul mootors&otilde;iduki juhtimise keelamine. </eesti>
<inglise>(1) Suspension of the right to drive means that a person is disqualified from driving motor vehicles. </inglise>
<eesti>(2) Juhtimis&otilde;iguse peatab politseiametnik v&otilde;i muu selleks seaduse alusel volitatud ametiisik v&otilde;i kohtunik. </eesti>
<inglise>(2) Police officers, other officials authorised therefor pursuant to law, and judges may suspend a person's right to drive. </inglise>
<eesti>(3) Juhtimis&otilde;igus peatatakse, kui: </eesti>
<inglise>(3) A person's right to drive shall be suspended if: </inglise>
<eesti>1) juht rikub k&auml;esoleva seaduse &sect; 20 l&otilde;igetes 2-5 ja 7 s&auml;testatut; </eesti>
<inglise>1) he or she violates the provisions of subsections 20 (2) -(5) or (7) of this Act; </inglise>
<eesti>2) juhiluba saadetakse ekspertiisi seoses juhiloa v&otilde;ltsingu kahtlusega; </eesti>
<inglise>2) his or her driving licence is sent for expert assessment due to suspicion regarding its authenticity; </inglise>
<eesti>3) juht ei sooritanud k&auml;esoleva seaduse &sect;-s 44 nimetatud liiklusteooria- v&otilde;i s&otilde;idueksamit; </eesti>
<inglise>3) he or she has not passed the theory test and driving test specified in &sect; 44 of this Act; </inglise>
<eesti>4) mootors&otilde;idukijuhi terviseseisund ei vasta k&auml;esoleva seaduse &sect; 28 l&otilde;ikes 2 nimetatud n&otilde;uetele. </eesti>
<inglise>4) his or her state of health does not meet the requirements specified in subsection 28 (2) of this Act. </inglise>
<eesti>(4) Juhtimis&otilde;igus peatub otsuse tegemisest arvates. </eesti>
<inglise>(4) The right to drive is suspended as of the decision being made. </inglise>
<eesti>(5) Juhtimis&otilde;iguse peatamise otsuses n&auml;idatakse &auml;ra juhtimis&otilde;iguse peatamise t&auml;htaeg v&otilde;i tingimus, mille t&auml;itmine on n&otilde;utav. </eesti>
<inglise>(5) A decision to suspend a person's right to drive shall set out the term for which his or her right to drive is suspended or a condition which shall be met. </inglise>
<eesti>(6) Juhtimis&otilde;iguse peatamist on p&auml;deval ametiisikul v&otilde;i kohtunikul &otilde;igus pikendada seadusega etten&auml;htud korras. </eesti>
<inglise>(6) A competent official or a judge has the right to extend the suspension of a person's right to drive pursuant to the procedure prescribed by law. </inglise>
<eesti>(7) Juhtimis&otilde;iguse peatamise korral on isik kohustatud juhiloa andma peatamisotsuse tegijale v&otilde;i tema nimetatud teisele ametiisikule. </eesti>
<inglise>(7) If a person's right to drive is suspended, he or she is required to hand his or her driving licence to the person who made the decision regarding suspension or to another official designated thereby. </inglise>
<eesti>(8) Juhtimis&otilde;iguse peatamise otsuse peale v&otilde;ib esitada kaebuse otsuse teinud ametiisiku k&otilde;rgemalseisvale ametiisikule v&otilde;i v&otilde;ib otsuse vaidlustada kohtus. </eesti>
<inglise>(8) A complaint may be filed against a decision to suspend a person's right to drive with an official who is superior to the official who made the decision, or the decision may be contested in court. </inglise>
<eesti>&sect; 42. </eesti>
<inglise>&sect; 42. </inglise>
<eesti>Juhtimis&otilde;iguse &auml;rav&otilde;tmine </eesti>
<inglise>Withdrawal of right to drive </inglise>
<eesti>Juhtimis&otilde;iguse &auml;rav&otilde;tmine on haldus- v&otilde;i kriminaalkaristus, mille sisuks on keeld juhtida mootors&otilde;idukit. </eesti>
<inglise>Withdrawal of the right to drive is an administrative or criminal punishment which entails disqualification from driving motor vehicles. </inglise>
<eesti>&sect; 43. </eesti>
<inglise>&sect; 43. </inglise>
<eesti>Juhtimis&otilde;iguse t&uuml;histamine </eesti>
<inglise>Cancellation of right to drive </inglise>
<eesti>(1) Juhtimis&otilde;igus t&uuml;histatakse, kui isik on juhtimis&otilde;iguse saanud pettuse teel v&otilde;i kui talle on juhiluba v&auml;lja antud v&otilde;ltsitud v&otilde;i valeandmeid sisaldava dokumendi alusel, samuti k&auml;esoleva seaduse &sect; 30 l&otilde;ikes 4 nimetatud juhul. </eesti>
<inglise>(1) A person's right to drive shall be cancelled if he or she obtained the right to drive by fraudulent means, if his or her driving licence was issued on the basis of a document containing falsified or false information, and in the case specified in subsection 30 (4) of this Act. </inglise>
<eesti>(2) Juhtimis&otilde;iguse t&uuml;histamise otsuse teeb asutus, kes on k&auml;esoleva seaduse alusel volitatud juhtimis&otilde;igust andma. </eesti>
<inglise>(2) A decision on the cancellation of a person's right to drive shall be made by an agency which is authorised to grant the right to drive pursuant to this Act. </inglise>
<eesti>(3) Juhtimis&otilde;iguse t&uuml;histamine j&otilde;ustub otsuse tegemisest arvates. </eesti>
<inglise>(3) Cancellation of a person's right to drive enters into force as of the decision being made. </inglise>
<eesti>(4) Juhtimis&otilde;iguse t&uuml;histamise otsuse teinud asutus teatab otsusest asjaomasele isikule t&auml;htkirjaga. </eesti>
<inglise>(4) An agency which makes a decision to cancel a person's right to drive shall notify the person concerned of the decision by registered letter. </inglise>
<eesti>(5) Juhtimis&otilde;iguse t&uuml;histamise korral on isik kohustatud loovutama juhiloa t&uuml;histamisotsuse tegijale v&otilde;i tema nimetatud teisele ametiisikule. </eesti>
<inglise>(5) If a person's right to drive is cancelled, he or she is required to hand his or her driving licence to the person who made the decision regarding cancellation or to another official designated thereby. </inglise>
<eesti>(6) Juhtimis&otilde;iguse t&uuml;histamise otsuse peale v&otilde;ib esitada kaebuse otsuse teinud ametiisiku k&otilde;rgemalseisvale ametiisikule v&otilde;i v&otilde;ib otsuse vaidlustada kohtus. </eesti>
<inglise>(6) A complaint may be filed against a decision to cancel a person's right to drive with an official who is superior to the official who made the decision, or the decision may be contested in court. </inglise>
<eesti>&sect; 44. </eesti>
<inglise>&sect; 44. </inglise>
<eesti>Juhtimis&otilde;iguse taastamine </eesti>
<inglise>Restoration of right to drive </inglise>
<eesti>(1) Kui isikult on juhtimis&otilde;igus &auml;ra v&otilde;etud rohkem kui kuueks kuuks, kuid mitte kauemaks kui 12 kuuks, saab ta taastada juhtimis&otilde;iguse juhul, kui ta sooritab edukalt liiklusteooriaeksami. </eesti>
<inglise>(1) If a person's right to drive has been withdrawn for longer than six months but not for longer than twelve months, his or her right to drive shall be restored if he or she passes the theory test. </inglise>
<eesti>(2) Kui isikult on juhtimis&otilde;igus &auml;ra v&otilde;etud kauemaks kui 12 kuuks, saab ta juhtimis&otilde;iguse taastada juhul, kui ta sooritab edukalt liiklusteooria- ja s&otilde;idueksami. </eesti>
<inglise>(2) If a person's right to drive has been withdrawn for longer than twelve months, his or her right to drive shall be restored if he or she passes the theory test and the driving test. </inglise>
<eesti>(3) Kui isik ei ole vahetanud juhiluba 12 kuu jooksul selle kehtivuse t&auml;htaja m&ouml;&ouml;dumisest arvates, saab ta juhtimis&otilde;iguse taastada juhul, kui ta sooritab edukalt liiklusteooria- ja s&otilde;idueksami. </eesti>
<inglise>(3) If a person has not replaced his or her driving licence within twelve months as of the expiry thereof, his or her right to drive shall be restored if he or she passes the theory test and the driving test. </inglise>
<eesti>9. peat&uuml;kk </eesti>
<inglise>Chapter 9 </inglise>
<eesti>Liikluse korraldamine ja liiklusj&auml;relevalve </eesti>
<inglise>Traffic Management and Traffic Supervision </inglise>
<eesti>&sect; 45. </eesti>
<inglise>&sect; 45. </inglise>
<eesti>Liikluse korraldamine </eesti>
<inglise>Traffic management </inglise>
<eesti>(1) Liikluse korraldamise eesm&auml;rk on tagada h&auml;ireteta, sujuv, v&otilde;imalikult kiire, ohutu ja keskkonda minimaalselt kahjustav liiklus. </eesti>
<inglise>(1) The purpose of traffic management is to ensure trouble-free, smooth, swift and safe traffic with minimum harm to the environment. </inglise>
<eesti>(2) Liikluse korraldamine toimub liiklusm&auml;rkide, teem&auml;rgiste, fooride, piirete ja muude liikluskorraldusvahenditega vastavalt teeseaduse alusel kehtestatud n&otilde;uetele. </eesti>
<inglise>(2) Traffic management is achieved through the use of traffic signs, road markings, traffic lights, barriers and other traffic management devices pursuant to the requirements established on the basis of the Roads Act. </inglise>
<eesti>(3) Liikluse korraldamise ning liikluskorraldusvahendite &otilde;ige paigutuse ja korrasoleku tagab teeomanik v&otilde;i teehoiu korraldamise eest vastutav isik. </eesti>
<inglise>(3) The owner of a road or a person responsible for the organisation of road management shall ensure traffic management and the proper positioning and maintenance of traffic management devices. </inglise>
<eesti>&sect; 46. </eesti>
<inglise>&sect; 46. </inglise>
<eesti>Liikluse reguleerimine ja liiklusj&auml;relevalve </eesti>
<inglise>Traffic control and traffic supervision </inglise>
<eesti>(1) Liiklusj&auml;relevalvet teostavad politseiametnikud, abipolitseinikud ja muud ametiisikud nendele seadusega antud volituste piires. </eesti>
<inglise>(1) Police officers, special constables or other officials shall exercise traffic supervision within the limits of the authority granted to them by law. </inglise>
<eesti>Riigipiiril kontrollivad mootors&otilde;idukeid ja nende haagiseid ning juhte piirivalve- ja tollit&ouml;&ouml;tajad. </eesti>
<inglise>On the state border, motor vehicles and their trailers and drivers shall be inspected by Border Guard and customs officials. </inglise>
<eesti>(2) Liikluse reguleerimise ja liiklusj&auml;relevalve teostamise korra kehtestab Vabariigi Valitsus. </eesti>
<inglise>(2) The procedure for traffic control and exercising traffic supervision shall be established by the Government of the Republic. </inglise>
<eesti>&sect; 47. </eesti>
<inglise>&sect; 47. </inglise>
<eesti>Lubatud s&otilde;idukiirus </eesti>
<inglise>Speed limit </inglise>
<eesti>(1) Suurim lubatud s&otilde;idukiirus asulav&auml;lisel teel on 90 kilomeetrit tunnis. </eesti>
<inglise>(1) The speed limit on roads outside built-up areas is 90 kilometres per hour. </inglise>
<eesti>(2) Suurim lubatud s&otilde;idukiirus asulasisesel teel on 50 kilomeetrit tunnis. </eesti>
<inglise>(2) The speed limit on roads in built-up areas is 50 kilometres per hour. </inglise>
<eesti>(3) Olenevalt liiklus- ja teeoludest, ohutusest ja s&otilde;iduki kategooriast v&otilde;ib teeomanik v&auml;hendada k&auml;esoleva paragrahvi l&otilde;igetes 1 ja 2 nimetatud suurimat lubatud s&otilde;idukiirust. </eesti>
<inglise>(3) Depending on the traffic and road conditions, safety and the category of vehicle, the owner of a road may reduce the speed limit specified in subsections (1) and (2) of this section. </inglise>
<eesti>(4) Olenevalt liiklus- ja teeoludest, ohutusest ja s&otilde;iduki kategooriast v&otilde;ib teede- ja sideministri kehtestatud tingimustel ja korras: </eesti>
<inglise>(4) Depending on the traffic and road conditions, safety and the category of vehicle, and under the conditions and pursuant to the procedure established by the Minister of Transport and Communications: </inglise>
<eesti>1) Maanteeamet suurendada asulav&auml;lisel teel suurimat lubatud s&otilde;idukiirust 120 kilomeetrini tunnis; </eesti>
<inglise>1) the Road Administration may increase the speed limit on roads outside built-up areas to up to 120 kilometres per hour; </inglise>
<eesti>2) kohalik omavalitsus suurendada asulasisesel teel suurimat lubatud s&otilde;idukiirust 90 kilomeetrini tunnis. </eesti>
<inglise>2) local governments may increase the speed limit on roads in built-up areas to up to 90 kilometres per hour. </inglise>
<eesti>(5) Juht peab kohandama oma s&otilde;iduki kiiruse selliseks, mis arvestab tema s&otilde;idukogemusi, teeolusid, tee ja s&otilde;iduki seisundit, veose ise&auml;rasusi, ilmastikutingimusi, liikluse tihedust ning muid liiklusolusid, et ta suudaks peatada s&otilde;iduki eespoolse n&auml;htavusulatuse piires ning teel etteaimatava mis tahes takistuse ees. </eesti>
<inglise>(5) A driver shall adapt the speed of his or her vehicle to his or her driving experience, the road conditions, the state of the road and the vehicle, the peculiarities of any goods carried, the weather conditions, the density of the traffic and other traffic conditions such that he or she is able to stop the vehicle within the area visible in front of the vehicle and without hitting any obstacle which can reasonably be expected to be on the road. </inglise>
<eesti>Juht peab v&auml;hendama kiirust ning vajaduse korral peatuma, kui tingimused seda n&otilde;uavad, eriti siis, kui n&auml;htavus on halb. </eesti>
<inglise>A driver shall reduce his or her speed and, if necessary, stop if the conditions so require, especially in poor visibility. </inglise>
<eesti>&sect; 48. </eesti>
<inglise>&sect; 48. </inglise>
<eesti>Piirangud mootors&otilde;idukite liiklusele </eesti>
<inglise>Restrictions on motor vehicle traffic </inglise>
<eesti>(1) Mootors&otilde;idukid, v&auml;lja arvatud eritalituse s&otilde;idukid, ei v&otilde;i s&otilde;ita, peatuda ega parkida v&auml;ljaspool teed kohtades, mis ei ole ette n&auml;htud mootors&otilde;idukite liikluseks. </eesti>
<inglise>(1) Motor vehicles, except emergency and road service vehicles, shall not be driven, stopped or parked off the road in places not intended for motor vehicle traffic. </inglise>
<eesti>Nendes kohtades v&otilde;ib liigelda ainult maaomaniku loal. </eesti>
<inglise>Traffic in such places is only permitted with the authorisation of the owner of the land. </inglise>
<eesti>(2) Mootors&otilde;idukid, v&auml;lja arvatud eritalituse s&otilde;idukid, ei v&otilde;i s&otilde;ita, peatuda ega parkida k&otilde;nniteedel, ohutussaartel, eraldusribadel, &otilde;uede ja teega k&uuml;lgnevate alade sisses&otilde;itudel. </eesti>
<inglise>(2) Motor vehicles, except emergency and road service vehicles, shall not be driven, stopped or parked on pavements, traffic islands, dividing strips, and entrances to areas adjacent to yards or roads. </inglise>
<eesti>(3) K&otilde;nniteel v&otilde;ib: </eesti>
<inglise>(3) On pavements, it is permitted: </inglise>
<eesti>1) peatuda ja parkida, kui see on liiklusm&auml;rkide v&otilde;i teem&auml;rgisega lubatud; </eesti>
<inglise>1) to stop and park if this is permitted by traffic signs or road markings; </inglise>
<eesti>2) peatuda ja parkida liikumispuudega juht, kelle s&otilde;idukil on k&auml;esoleva seaduse lisa 2 kohane parkimiskaart; </eesti>
<inglise>2) for physically disabled drivers whose vehicles display parking cards in the format set out in Annex 2 to this Act to stop and park; </inglise>
<eesti>3) peatuda veose laadimiseks, kuid mitte l&auml;hemal kui 15 meetrit &uuml;hiss&otilde;idukite peatuskohast. </eesti>
<inglise>3) to stop to load goods if the vehicle is not stopped less than fifteen metres from a public transport stopping point. </inglise>
<eesti>(4) K&auml;esoleva paragrahvi l&otilde;ikes 3 nimetatud peatumise ja parkimise korral peab jalak&auml;ijale j&auml;&auml;ma vabaks v&auml;hemalt 1,5 meetri laiune k&auml;iguriba. </eesti>
<inglise>(4) If a vehicle is stopped or parked in a manner specified in subsection (3) of this section, a strip of pavement at least 1.5 metres wide shall be left for pedestrians to use. </inglise>
<eesti>&sect; 49. </eesti>
<inglise>&sect; 49. </inglise>
<eesti>Liiklus &otilde;uealal </eesti>
<inglise>Traffic in calm traffic areas </inglise>
<eesti>(1) Jalak&auml;ija v&otilde;ib &otilde;uealal liikuda kogu tee ulatuses. </eesti>
<inglise>(1) In calm traffic areas, pedestrians may use the whole road. </inglise>
<eesti>(2) Juht ei v&otilde;i &otilde;uealal jalak&auml;ijat ohustada ega takistada, vajaduse korral tuleb s&otilde;iduk peatada. </eesti>
<inglise>(2) Drivers shall not endanger or obstruct pedestrians in calm traffic areas and, if necessary, they shall stop their vehicles. </inglise>
<eesti>Jalak&auml;ija ei v&otilde;i juhti p&otilde;hjendamatult takistada. </eesti>
<inglise>Pedestrians shall not obstruct drivers unnecessarily. </inglise>
<eesti>(3) S&otilde;iduk v&otilde;ib &otilde;uealal jalak&auml;ijate vahetus l&auml;heduses liikuda jalak&auml;ija kiirusega ja mujal mitte kiiremini kui 20 kilomeetrit tunnis. </eesti>
<inglise>(3) In a calm traffic area, a vehicle may be driven at the speed of pedestrians if there are pedestrians in the immediate vicinity of the vehicle and elsewhere not faster than 20 kilometres per hour. </inglise>
<eesti>(4) Mootors&otilde;iduk v&otilde;ib &otilde;uealale s&otilde;ita vaid peatumiseks v&otilde;i parkimiseks. </eesti>
<inglise>(4) A motor vehicle may enter a calm traffic area only to stop or park. </inglise>
<eesti>(5) &Otilde;uealal v&otilde;ib parkida ainult A- ja B-kategooria ning D1-alamkategooria s&otilde;idukit. </eesti>
<inglise>(5) Only vehicles in categories A or B or subcategory D1 may be parked in a calm traffic area. </inglise>
<eesti>Parkida v&otilde;ib ainult t&auml;histatud parklas v&otilde;i teel kohas, kus parkimine ei takista jalak&auml;ijat ega muuda v&otilde;imatuks teiste s&otilde;idukite liiklust. </eesti>
<inglise>Parking is permitted only in marked car-parks or on the road in places where the parked vehicle does not obstruct pedestrians or render other vehicular traffic impossible. </inglise>
<eesti>&sect; 50. </eesti>
<inglise>&sect; 50. </inglise>
<eesti>Parkimise korraldamine </eesti>
<inglise>Organisation of parking </inglise>
<eesti>(1) Parkimine on s&otilde;iduki ettekavatsetud seismaj&auml;tmine kauemaks, kui seda on vaja s&otilde;itjate peale- v&otilde;i mahaminekuks v&otilde;i veose laadimiseks. </eesti>
<inglise>(1) Parking is the bringing of a vehicle to an intentional halt for longer than is necessary to pick up or set down passengers or for goods to be loaded. </inglise>
<eesti>(2) Parkimine peab olema korraldatud nii, et see ei h&auml;iri ega ohusta liiklust ega p&otilde;hjusta elamupiirkonnas inimeste h&auml;irimist mootors&otilde;idukite heitgaasi ja m&uuml;raga. </eesti>
<inglise>(2) Parking shall be organised so as not to disturb or endanger traffic or cause disturbance to people in residential areas as a result of motor vehicle exhaust gases and noise. </inglise>
<eesti>(3) Liiklust h&auml;irivalt v&otilde;i ohustavalt pargitud s&otilde;iduki v&otilde;ib parkimist korraldav teeomanik v&otilde;i teehoiu eest vastutav isik lasta &uuml;mber paigutada valvega hoiukohta seadusega etten&auml;htud korras. </eesti>
<inglise>(3) The owner of a road who organises parking or a person responsible for road management may have a vehicle which is parked such that it disturbs or endangers traffic relocated to a guarded storage facility pursuant to the procedure prescribed by law. </inglise>
<eesti>&Uuml;mberpaigutamis- ja hoidmiskulud tasub s&otilde;iduki kasutaja. </eesti>
<inglise>Towing and storage charges shall be paid by the user of the vehicle. </inglise>
<eesti>(4) Parkimist korraldab teeomanik v&otilde;i teehoiu korraldamise eest vastutav isik liiklusm&auml;rkide, teem&auml;rgiste ning muude liikluskorraldusvahendite abil. </eesti>
<inglise>(4) Parking shall be organised by the owner of a road or a person responsible for the organisation of road management by means of traffic signs, road markings and other traffic management devices. </inglise>
<eesti>(5) Teeomanik v&otilde;i teehoiu korraldamise eest vastutav isik v&otilde;ib kehtestada tasulise parkimise. </eesti>
<inglise>(5) The owner of a road or a person responsible for the organisation of road management may charge a fee for parking. </inglise>
<eesti>&sect; 51. </eesti>
<inglise>&sect; 51. </inglise>
<eesti>Pargitud s&otilde;iduki &uuml;mberpaigutamine erandolukorras </eesti>
<inglise>Relocation of parked vehicles in exceptional circumstances </inglise>
<eesti>(1) Erandolukorras, mis on tingitud kiiresti muutuvatest ilmastikuoludest, vajadusest t&auml;ita operatiiv&uuml;lesandeid v&otilde;i muust liikluskorra muutmise vajadusest, v&otilde;idakse muuta parkimise korraldust. </eesti>
<inglise>(1) In exceptional circumstances caused by rapidly changing weather conditions, the need to perform operational tasks or any other need to alter the road traffic rules, the organisation of parking may be changed. </inglise>
<eesti>(2) Erandolukorrast tingitud parkimiskorralduse muutmisel fikseerib parkimist korraldav ametnik seni &otilde;igusp&auml;raselt pargitud s&otilde;idukid ning need paigutatakse &uuml;mber valvega hoiukohta seadusega etten&auml;htud korras. </eesti>
<inglise>(2) If the organisation of parking is changed due to exceptional circumstances, the official who regulates parking shall document the vehicles which have been parked legitimately and they will be relocated to a guarded storage facility pursuant to the procedure provided by law. </inglise>
<eesti>&Uuml;mberpaigutamis- ja hoidmiskulud tasub parkimist korraldav asutus. </eesti>
<inglise>Towing and storage charges shall be paid by the agency which organises parking. </inglise>
<eesti>&sect; 52. </eesti>
<inglise>&sect; 52. </inglise>
<eesti>Keskkonnakaitsen&otilde;uded </eesti>
<inglise>Environmental protection requirements </inglise>
<eesti>(1) Juht ei v&otilde;i kahjustada keskkonda s&otilde;iduki mootori v&otilde;i teiste seadmete p&otilde;hjustatud liigse m&uuml;ra, tolmu v&otilde;i heitgaasiga, mida oleks v&otilde;imalik v&auml;ltida. </eesti>
<inglise>(1) Drivers shall not damage the environment with excessive noise, dust or exhaust gases produced by the engine or other devices of vehicles if it is possible to avoid such damage. </inglise>
<eesti>(2) Mootors&otilde;idukit ei v&otilde;i pesta veekogus ega kaldal l&auml;hemal kui 10 meetrit veepiirist. </eesti>
<inglise>(2) Motor vehicles shall not be washed in bodies of water or on the shore closer than 10 metres to the shore-line. </inglise>
<eesti>(3) Liikleja ei v&otilde;i: </eesti>
<inglise>(3) Road users shall not: </inglise>
<eesti>1) saastada keskkonda k&uuml;tte- v&otilde;i m&auml;&auml;rdeainetega ega vahetada mootors&otilde;idukil &otilde;li kohas, mis ei ole selleks ette n&auml;htud; </eesti>
<inglise>1) contaminate the environment with fuel or lubricants or change the oil of a motor vehicle in a place which is not designated therefor; </inglise>
<eesti>2) kahjustada, risustada v&otilde;i muul viisil saastada teed ega teega k&uuml;lgnevat ala; </eesti>
<inglise>2) damage, pollute or otherwise contaminate roads or areas adjacent to roads; </inglise>
<eesti>3) liigelda s&otilde;idukiga, millel on keskkonda saastav leke. </eesti>
<inglise>3) use vehicles with a leak which contaminates the environment. </inglise>
<eesti>(4) S&otilde;iduki mootori heitgaasi saasteainesisaldus ega m&uuml;ratase ei v&otilde;i &uuml;letada keskkonnaministri kehtestatud normi. </eesti>
<inglise>(4) The level of pollutants in exhaust emissions and the noise level of vehicle engines shall not exceed the standards established by the Minister of the Environment. </inglise>
<eesti>(5) &Otilde;uealal ja elamupiirkonnas ei v&otilde;i seisva s&otilde;iduki mootor t&ouml;&ouml;tada kauem kui kaks minutit. </eesti>
<inglise>(5) The engines of vehicles standing in calm traffic areas or residential areas shall not be left switched on for more than two minutes. </inglise>
<eesti>10. peat&uuml;kk </eesti>
<inglise>Chapter 10 </inglise>
<eesti>Liikumispuudega inimeste liiklemise tagamine </eesti>
<inglise>Ensurance of Road Mobility for Physically Disabled People </inglise>
<eesti>&sect; 53. </eesti>
<inglise>&sect; 53. </inglise>
<eesti>Liikumispuudega inimeste liiklemise ja neid teenindavate s&otilde;idukite parkimise korraldamine </eesti>
<inglise>Organisation of road mobility for physically disabled people and parking for vehicles servicing such people </inglise>
<eesti>(1) Liikumispuudega v&otilde;i pimedate inimeste liiklemist ja neid teenindavate s&otilde;idukite parkimist ning liikumispuudega inimeste juhitavate s&otilde;idukite parkimist korraldab kohalik omavalitsus. </eesti>
<inglise>(1) Road mobility for physically disabled or blind people, parking for vehicles servicing such people and parking for vehicles driven by physically disabled people shall be organised by local governments. </inglise>
<eesti>(2) Liikumispuudega juht v&otilde;ib tema kasutuses olevat s&otilde;idukit k&auml;esoleva seaduse lisa 2 kohase parkimiskaardi olemasolul parkida avalikes tasulistes parkimiskohtades tasuta. </eesti>
<inglise>(2) If a physically disabled driver has a parking card in the format set out in Annex 2 to this Act, he or she may park his or her vehicle in public fee-paying parking places without charge. </inglise>
<eesti>(3) Liikumispuudega inimene, kes liigub inimj&otilde;ul v&otilde;i mootori j&otilde;ul, kuid jalak&auml;ija kiirusega liikuva ratastooliga, v&otilde;ib kasutada k&otilde;nniteed v&otilde;i selleks k&otilde;lblikku teepeenart. </eesti>
<inglise>(3) A physically disabled person travelling at the speed of a pedestrian in a non-power-driven or power-driven wheelchair may use the pavement or a suitable verge. </inglise>
<eesti>&sect; 54. </eesti>
<inglise>&sect; 54. </inglise>
<eesti>Liikumispuudega inimese s&otilde;iduki parkimiskaart </eesti>
<inglise>Parking cards for people with physical disabilities </inglise>
<eesti>(1) Liikumispuudega v&otilde;i pimeda inimese liiklemise tagamiseks antakse talle k&auml;esoleva seaduse lisa 2 kohane teda teenindava s&otilde;iduki parkimiskaart. </eesti>
<inglise>(1) In order to ensure road mobility for a physically disabled or blind person, a parking card for a vehicle servicing him or her shall be issued to him or her in the format set out in Annex 2 to this Act. </inglise>
<eesti>(2) Liikumispuudega v&otilde;i pimedat inimest teenindava s&otilde;iduki parkimiskaartide tr&uuml;kkimist korraldab ja v&auml;ljaandmise tingimused kehtestab sotsiaalminister. </eesti>
<inglise>(2) The printing of parking cards for vehicles servicing physically disabled or blind people shall be organised and the conditions for the issue thereof shall be established by the Minister of Social Affairs. </inglise>
<eesti>(3) Parkimiskaardi v&auml;ljaandmise aluseks on arsti teatis. </eesti>
<inglise>(3) The basis for the issue of a parking card is a medical certificate. </inglise>
<eesti>(4) Parkimiskaardi annab v&auml;lja kohalik omavalitsus. </eesti>
<inglise>(4) Parking cards shall be issued by local governments. </inglise>
<eesti>&sect; 55. </eesti>
<inglise>&sect; 55. </inglise>
<eesti>Liikumispuudega juhi ja liikumispuudega v&otilde;i pimedat inimest teenindava s&otilde;iduki juhi eri&otilde;igused </eesti>
<inglise>Special rights of physically disabled drivers and drivers of vehicles servicing physically disabled or blind people </inglise>
<eesti>(1) Liikumispuudega juht ja liikumispuudega v&otilde;i pimedat inimest teenindava s&otilde;iduki juht v&otilde;ib panna oma s&otilde;iduki esi- v&otilde;i tagaklaasile k&auml;esoleva seaduse lisa 2 kohase parkimiskaardi. </eesti>
<inglise>(1) A physically disabled driver and a driver of a vehicle servicing physically disabled or blind people may attach a parking card in the format set out in Annex 2 to this Act to the front or rear window of his or her vehicle. </inglise>
<eesti>(2) Liikumispuudega juht, kelle s&otilde;idukil on k&auml;esoleva seaduse lisa 2 kohane parkimiskaart, v&otilde;ib: </eesti>
<inglise>(2) A physically disabled driver whose vehicle displays a parking card in the format set out in Annex 2 to this Act may: </inglise>
<eesti>1) asulas peatuda ja parkida peatumist v&otilde;i parkimist keelavate liiklusm&auml;rkide m&otilde;jupiirkonnas tingimusel, et seisev s&otilde;iduk asub t&auml;ielikult k&otilde;nniteel, j&auml;ttes jalak&auml;ijale seal vabaks v&auml;hemalt 1,5 meetri laiuse k&auml;iguriba. </eesti>
<inglise>1) stop and park in built-up areas where traffic signs apply which prohibit stopping or parking, on the condition that the standing vehicle is located entirely on the pavement and that a strip of pavement at least 1.5 metres wide is left for pedestrians to use. </inglise>
<eesti>Kirjeldatud luba ei kehti teel&otilde;igul, mis on t&auml;histatud peatumise keelujoonega; </eesti>
<inglise>This permission does not apply on sections of road marked with a no stopping line; </inglise>
<eesti>2) parkida parkimist keelavate liiklusm&auml;rkide m&otilde;jupiirkonnas, piiratud parkimisajaga parklas etten&auml;htust kauem ja &otilde;ueala teel v&auml;ljaspool parklat kohas, kus see ei takista jalak&auml;ijaid ega muuda v&otilde;imatuks teiste s&otilde;idukite liiklust. </eesti>
<inglise>2) park in areas where traffic signs apply which prohibit parking, in car-parks with limited parking time for longer than prescribed, and on roads in calm traffic areas outside car-parks in places where this does not obstruct pedestrians or render other vehicular traffic impossible. </inglise>
<eesti>(3) Liikumispuudega v&otilde;i pimedat inimest teenindava s&otilde;iduki juht, kelle s&otilde;idukil on k&auml;esoleva seaduse lisa 2 kohane parkimiskaart, v&otilde;ib asulas peatuda peatumist keelavate liiklusm&auml;rkide m&otilde;jupiirkonnas liikumispuudega v&otilde;i pimeda inimese s&otilde;idukisse pealev&otilde;tmiseks v&otilde;i s&otilde;idukist v&auml;ljalaskmiseks. </eesti>
<inglise>(3) A driver of a vehicle servicing a physically disabled or blind person whose vehicle displays a parking card in the format set out in Annex 2 to this Act may stop in built-up areas where traffic signs apply which prohibit stopping in order to pick up or set down the physically disabled or blind person. </inglise>
<eesti>(4) Liikumispuudega v&otilde;i pimedat inimest teenindava s&otilde;iduki juht, kelle s&otilde;idukil on k&auml;esoleva seaduse lisa 2 kohane parkimiskaart ja kes talutab liikumispuudega v&otilde;i pimedat inimest soovitud kohta ja tagasi, v&otilde;ib asulas peatuda k&auml;esoleva paragrahvi l&otilde;ike 2 punktis 1 nimetatud tingimustel. </eesti>
<inglise>(4) A driver of a vehicle servicing a physically disabled or blind person whose vehicle displays a parking card in the format set out in Annex 2 to this Act and who leads the physically disabled or blind person to the desired place and back may stop in built-up areas under the conditions specified in clause (2) 1) of this section. </inglise>
<eesti>11. peat&uuml;kk </eesti>
<inglise>Chapter 11 </inglise>
<eesti>Liiklus&otilde;nnetus </eesti>
<inglise>Traffic Accident </inglise>
<eesti>&sect; 56. </eesti>
<inglise>&sect; 56. </inglise>
<eesti>Liiklus&otilde;nnetuse m&otilde;iste </eesti>
<inglise>Definition of traffic accident </inglise>
<eesti>Liiklus&otilde;nnetus on juhtum, kus v&auml;hemalt &uuml;he s&otilde;iduki teel liikumise v&otilde;i teelt v&auml;ljas&otilde;idu tagaj&auml;rjel saab inimene vigastada v&otilde;i surma v&otilde;i tekib varaline kahju. </eesti>
<inglise>A traffic accident is an event in which an individual is injured or killed or proprietary damage is caused as a result of at least one vehicle moving on or leaving a road. </inglise>
<eesti>&sect; 57. </eesti>
<inglise>&sect; 57. </inglise>
<eesti>&Uuml;ldine abistamiskohustus </eesti>
<inglise>General duty to assist </inglise>
<eesti>Iga juht on kohustatud abistama liiklus&otilde;nnetuses kannatada saanud abitus seisundis olevat inimest. </eesti>
<inglise>Every driver is required to assist any person who is in need of assistance due to a traffic accident. </inglise>
<eesti>Kui kannatanu abistamiseks on vaja ta kohe toimetada haiglasse ja kui kannatanu seisukord v&otilde;imaldab teda transportida, siis peab juht seda tegema. </eesti>
<inglise>If it is necessary to take a victim immediately to hospital in order to assist him or her and if the state of the victim allows him or her to be transported, the driver shall act accordingly. </inglise>
<eesti>Kui s&otilde;iduk ei sobi kannatanu ohutuks transportimiseks, peab selle juht aitama korraldada kannatanu toimetamist haiglasse muu sobiva s&otilde;idukiga. </eesti>
<inglise>If the vehicle is not suitable for the safe transportation of the victim, the driver thereof shall help organise the transportation of the victim to hospital using another suitable vehicle. </inglise>
<eesti>&sect; 58. </eesti>
<inglise>&sect; 58. </inglise>
<eesti>S&otilde;idukijuhi tegevus liiklus&otilde;nnetuse s&uuml;ndmuskohal ja liiklus&otilde;nnetusest teatamine </eesti>
<inglise>Action taken by driver of vehicle at site of traffic accident and notification of traffic accident </inglise>
<eesti>Liiklus&otilde;nnetuse s&uuml;ndmuskohal s&otilde;idukijuhi tegevuse ja liiklus&otilde;nnetusest teatamise korra kehtestab Vabariigi Valitsus. </eesti>
<inglise>The procedure for action to be taken by a driver of a vehicle at the site of a traffic accident and for notification of traffic accidents shall be established by the Government of the Republic. </inglise>
<eesti>&sect; 59. </eesti>
<inglise>&sect; 59. </inglise>
<eesti>P&auml;&auml;stet&ouml;&ouml;d </eesti>
<inglise>Rescue operations </inglise>
<eesti>(1) Liiklus&otilde;nnetuse s&uuml;ndmuskohal teostab tulekustutus- ja p&auml;&auml;stet&ouml;id p&auml;&auml;steasutus. </eesti>
<inglise>(1) Fire extinguishing and rescue work at the site of a traffic accident shall be conducted by a rescue service agency. </inglise>
<eesti>(2) Liiklus&otilde;nnetuse s&uuml;ndmuskohal korraldab hukkunute &auml;ravedu politsei. </eesti>
<inglise>(2) Transportation of the deceased from the site of a traffic accident shall be organised by the police. </inglise>
<eesti>(3) Kui s&otilde;idukijuht sai liiklus&otilde;nnetuses surma v&otilde;i selliselt vigastada, et ta toimetati raviasutusse, korraldab tema s&otilde;iduki liiklus&otilde;nnetuse s&uuml;ndmuskohalt &auml;raviimise ja tagab selle s&auml;ilimise politsei. </eesti>
<inglise>(3) If the driver of a vehicle is killed in a traffic accident or is injured such that he or she is taken to a medical institution, the transportation of the vehicle from the site of the traffic accident shall be arranged and the preservation thereof shall be ensured by the police. </inglise>
<eesti>&sect; 60. </eesti>
<inglise>&sect; 60. </inglise>
<eesti>Liiklus&otilde;nnetuse asjaolude v&auml;ljaselgitamine ja arvestus </eesti>
<inglise>Identification of circumstances of and keeping records on traffic accidents </inglise>
<eesti>Liiklus&otilde;nnetuse asjaolude v&auml;ljaselgitamise, vormistamise, registreerimise ja arvestuse korra kehtestab Vabariigi Valitsus. </eesti>
<inglise>The procedure for the identification of circumstances and for the formalisation, registration and keeping of records on traffic accidents shall be established by the Government of the Republic. </inglise>
<eesti>&sect; 61. </eesti>
<inglise>&sect; 61. </inglise>
<eesti>Ekspertkomisjon </eesti>
<inglise>Expert committee </inglise>
<eesti>(1) Liiklus&otilde;nnetuse p&otilde;hjuste v&auml;ljaselgitamiseks, &uuml;ldistamiseks ja liiklusohutuse tagamise ettepanekute v&auml;ljat&ouml;&ouml;tamiseks v&otilde;ib teede- ja sideminister moodustada ekspertkomisjone. </eesti>
<inglise>(1) The Minister of Transport and Communications may form expert committees in order to ascertain and generalise the causes of traffic accidents and to develop proposals for the ensurance of road traffic safety. </inglise>
<eesti>(2) Ekspertkomisjonil on &otilde;igus tutvuda liiklus&otilde;nnetuse kohta koostatud materjalidega, selgitada v&auml;lja liiklus&otilde;nnetuse asjaolusid, koostada &uuml;ldistusi ja teha ettepanekuid liiklusohutuse parandamiseks, liiklus&otilde;nnetuste tekkep&otilde;hjuste k&otilde;rvaldamiseks ja liiklus&otilde;nnetuste tagaj&auml;rgede leevendamiseks. </eesti>
<inglise>(2) An expert committee has the right to examine materials prepared on a traffic accident, ascertain the circumstances of the traffic accident, prepare generalisations, and make proposals for the improvement of road traffic safety, elimination of the causes of traffic accidents and mitigation of the consequences of traffic accidents. </inglise>
<eesti>12. peat&uuml;kk </eesti>
<inglise>Chapter 12 </inglise>
<eesti>Liiklusregister. </eesti>
<inglise>Traffic Register. </inglise>
<eesti>Riigiv&otilde;imu teostamine s&otilde;idukite ja juhilubadega seotud toimingute puhul </eesti>
<inglise>Exercise of State Authority in cases of Acts related to Vehicles and Driving Licences </inglise>
<eesti>&sect; 62. </eesti>
<inglise>&sect; 62. </inglise>
<eesti>Liiklusregister </eesti>
<inglise>Traffic register </inglise>
<eesti>(1) Liiklusregister on Vabariigi Valitsuse poolt teede- ja sideministri ettepanekul asutatud riiklik register andmekogude seaduse (RT I 1997, 28, 423; 1998, 36/37, 552; 1999, 10, 155; 2000, 50, 317; 57, 373; 92, 597) t&auml;henduses, mille pidamise eesm&auml;rk on s&otilde;idukite (v&auml;lja arvatud kaitsej&otilde;udude s&otilde;idukid), juhilubade ja muude juhtimis&otilde;igust t&otilde;endavate dokumentide &uuml;le arvestuse pidamine. </eesti>
<inglise>(1) The traffic register is a state register which is established by the Government of the Republic on the proposal of the Minister of Transport and Communications within the meaning of the Databases Act (RT I 1997, 28, 423; 1998, 36/37, 552; 1999, 10, 155; 2000, 50, 317; 57, 373; 92, 597) with the aim of maintaining records on vehicles (except vehicles of the Defence Forces), driving licences and other documents certifying the right to drive. </inglise>
<eesti>(2) Liiklusregister on &uuml;hetasandiline riiklik register. </eesti>
<inglise>(2) The traffic register is a single-level state register. </inglise>
<eesti>(3) Liiklusregistri vastutav t&ouml;&ouml;tleja on Teede- ja Sideministeerium ning volitatud t&ouml;&ouml;tleja teede- ja sideministri m&auml;&auml;ratud asutus. </eesti>
<inglise>(3) The chief processor of the traffic register is the Ministry of Transport and Communications, and the authorised processor of the traffic register is an agency designated by the Minister of Transport and Communications. </inglise>
<eesti>&sect; 63. </eesti>
<inglise>&sect; 63. </inglise>
<eesti>Liiklusregistri andmebaasid </eesti>
<inglise>Databases in traffic register </inglise>
<eesti>(1) Liiklusregister koosneb: </eesti>
<inglise>(1) The traffic register is composed of: </inglise>
<eesti>1) s&otilde;idukite andmebaasist; </eesti>
<inglise>1) the vehicle database; </inglise>
<eesti>2) juhilubade andmebaasist. </eesti>
<inglise>2) the driving licence database. </inglise>
<eesti>(2) S&otilde;idukite andmebaasis peetakse arvestust Eestis registreeritud mootors&otilde;idukite, nende haagiste ja k&auml;esoleva seaduse &sect;-s 68 nimetatud maastikus&otilde;idukite ning nende omanike ja &otilde;igustatud kasutajate, samuti s&otilde;idukite kasutamisele seatud piirangute &uuml;le. </eesti>
<inglise>(2) In the vehicle database, records shall be maintained on motor vehicles registered in Estonia, their trailers, all-terrain vehicles specified in &sect; 68 of this Act, the owners and entitled users thereof, and restrictions on the use of the vehicles. </inglise>
<eesti>(3) Juhilubade andmebaasis peetakse arvestust juhtimis&otilde;iguse andmise, peatamise, &auml;rav&otilde;tmise, t&uuml;histamise ja taastamise, samuti Eestis v&auml;ljaantud juhilubade ja muude juhtimis&otilde;igust t&otilde;endavate dokumentide &uuml;le. </eesti>
<inglise>(3) In the driving licence database, records shall be maintained on the grant, suspension, withdrawal, cancellation and restoration of the right to drive, driving licences issued in Estonia and other documents certifying the right to drive. </inglise>
<eesti>&sect; 64. </eesti>
<inglise>&sect; 64. </inglise>
<eesti>Liiklusregistrisse andmete esitajad </eesti>
<inglise>Persons submitting information to traffic register </inglise>
<eesti>(1) Liiklusregistrisse andmete esitajaks on: </eesti>
<inglise>(1) The following shall submit information to the traffic register: </inglise>
<eesti>1) s&otilde;iduki omanik v&otilde;i tema esindaja; </eesti>
<inglise>1) owners of vehicles or representatives thereof; </inglise>
<eesti>2) juhtimis&otilde;iguse v&otilde;i juhiloa taotleja; </eesti>
<inglise>2) applicants for the right to drive or a driving licence; </inglise>
<eesti>3) ametiasutus v&otilde;i kohus juhtimis&otilde;iguse peatamisel, &auml;rav&otilde;tmisel ja t&uuml;histamisel; </eesti>
<inglise>3) administrative agencies or courts upon suspension, withdrawal or cancellation of the right to drive; </inglise>
<eesti>4) k&auml;sutamispiiranguid kohaldama &otilde;igustatud isikud. </eesti>
<inglise>4) persons entitled to apply restrictions on transfer. </inglise>
<eesti>(2) K&auml;esolevas seaduses etten&auml;htud &uuml;lesannete t&auml;itmiseks on teede- ja sideministri m&auml;&auml;ratud asutusel &otilde;igus n&otilde;uda ja seadustes nimetatud andmete esitajatel kohustus esitada t&otilde;eseid andmeid &otilde;igusaktidega kehtestatud tingimustel ja korras. </eesti>
<inglise>(2) In order to perform the functions prescribed in this Act, an agency designated by the Minister of Transport and Communications has the right to request submission of true information and persons specified by law who submit information are required to submit true information, under the conditions and pursuant to the procedure established by legislation. </inglise>
<eesti>(3) Ametiasutus v&otilde;i kohus, kes on teinud otsuse isikult mootors&otilde;iduki v&otilde;i trammi juhtimise &otilde;iguse &auml;rav&otilde;tmise kohta, saadab otsuse &auml;rakirja teede- ja sideministri m&auml;&auml;ratud asutusele hiljemalt j&auml;rgmisel t&ouml;&ouml;p&auml;eval otsuse tegemisest arvates. </eesti>
<inglise>(3) An administrative agency or a court which makes a decision or judgment on the withdrawal of a person's right to drive a motor vehicle or tram shall send a copy of the decision or judgment to the agency designated by the Minister of Transport and Communications not later than on the next working day as of the decision or judgment being made. </inglise>
<eesti>&sect; 65. </eesti>
<inglise>&sect; 65. </inglise>
<eesti>Juurdep&auml;&auml;s liiklusregistrisse kantud andmetele </eesti>
<inglise>Access to information entered in traffic register </inglise>
<eesti>(1) F&uuml;&uuml;silisel ja juriidilisel isikul on &otilde;igus juurde p&auml;&auml;seda &uuml;ksnes nendega seotud registriandmetele. </eesti>
<inglise>(1) Natural and legal persons only have the right to access information in the register which relates to them. </inglise>
<eesti>(2) Riigi- ja kohaliku omavalitsuse asutusel on &otilde;igus juurde p&auml;&auml;seda seadustekohaste &uuml;lesannete t&auml;itmiseks vajalikele andmetele. </eesti>
<inglise>(2) State and local government agencies have the right to access information which is necessary for the performance of their functions in accordance with law. </inglise>
<eesti>Riigiga lepingu alusel avalikku &uuml;lesannet t&auml;itval isikul on &otilde;igus juurde p&auml;&auml;seda andmetele, mis on talle vajalikud avalike &uuml;lesannete t&auml;itmiseks. </eesti>
<inglise>Persons performing public duties on the basis of a contract with the state have the right to access information which is necessary for them to perform their public duties. </inglise>
<eesti>(3) Teaduslikul eesm&auml;rgil v&otilde;i muu &otilde;igustatud huvi puhul andmetele juurdep&auml;&auml;su korra kehtestab registri vastutav t&ouml;&ouml;tleja. </eesti>
<inglise>(3) The procedure for accessing information for scientific purposes or in the case of other legitimate interests shall be established by the chief processor of the register. </inglise>
<eesti>&sect; 66. </eesti>
<inglise>&sect; 66. </inglise>
<eesti>Riigiv&otilde;imu teostamine s&otilde;idukite ja juhilubadega seotud toimingute puhul </eesti>
<inglise>Exercise of state authority in cases of acts related to vehicles and driving licences </inglise>
<eesti>(1) Teede- ja sideminister m&auml;&auml;rab asutuse, kes riigiv&otilde;imu teostamisel: </eesti>
<inglise>(1) The Minister of Transport and Communications shall designate an agency which, upon exercising state authority, shall: </inglise>
<eesti>1) korraldab mootors&otilde;iduki ja trammi juhtimise &otilde;iguse saamiseks v&otilde;i taastamiseks n&otilde;utavad eksamid ja otsustab eksamitulemused, annab mootors&otilde;iduki ja trammi juhtimise &otilde;iguse ning annab v&auml;lja, vahetab ja n&otilde;uab tagasi juhilube; </eesti>
<inglise>1) organise the tests required in order for a person to obtain the right to drive motor vehicles or trams or for such right to be restored to him or her, and shall decide on test results, grant the right to drive motor vehicles or trams and issue, replace and demand the return of driving licences; </inglise>
<eesti>2) t&uuml;histab juhtimis&otilde;iguse seadusega etten&auml;htud juhtudel ja tingimustel; </eesti>
<inglise>2) cancel a person's right to drive in the cases and under the conditions prescribed by law; </inglise>
<eesti>3) korraldab ja teostab mootors&otilde;idukite, trammide ja nende haagiste ning nende osade ja varustuse tehnilist ekspertiisi, katsetamist ja t&uuml;&uuml;bikinnitamist; </eesti>
<inglise>3) organise and conduct the technical expert analysis, testing and type approval of motor vehicles, trams, their trailers and their parts and equipment; </inglise>
<eesti>4) korraldab ja teostab maastikus&otilde;idukite ning nende osade ja varustuse tehnilist ekspertiisi ja katsetamist; </eesti>
<inglise>4) organise and conduct the technical expert analysis and testing of all-terrain vehicles and their parts and equipment; </inglise>
<eesti>5) korraldab ja teostab mootors&otilde;idukite, trammide ja nende haagiste ning maastikus&otilde;idukite varustuse tehnoseisundi n&otilde;uetele vastavuse kontrolli; </eesti>
<inglise>5) organise and conduct inspection of the roadworthiness and fitness for service of motor vehicles, trams, their trailers and the equipment of all-terrain vehicles; </inglise>
<eesti>6) registreerib mootors&otilde;idukeid, nende haagiseid ja maastikus&otilde;idukeid, v&auml;ljastab nende registreerimism&auml;rke ja registreerimistunnistusi ning vormistab registrimuudatusi. </eesti>
<inglise>6) register motor vehicles, their trailers and all-terrain vehicles, issue the registration plates and registration certificates and formalise changes in the register. </inglise>
<eesti>(2) Teede- ja sideminister v&otilde;ib volitada tema m&auml;&auml;ratud asutust s&otilde;lmima &auml;ri&uuml;hingutega lepinguid mootors&otilde;idukite, trammide ja nende haagiste ning maastikus&otilde;idukite tehnoseisundi n&otilde;uetele vastavuse kontrollimiseks. </eesti>
<inglise>(2) The Minister of Transport and Communications may authorise the agency designated thereby to enter into contracts with companies to inspect the roadworthiness and fitness for service of motor vehicles, trams, their trailers and all-terrain vehicles. </inglise>
<eesti>Lepingu kohustuslikud tingimused kehtestab teede- ja sideminister. </eesti>
<inglise>The mandatory terms and conditions for such contracts shall be established by the Minister of Transport and Communications. </inglise>
<eesti>&sect; 67. </eesti>
<inglise>&sect; 67. </inglise>
<eesti>S&otilde;iduki tehnoseisundit kontrollivale &auml;ri&uuml;hingule esitatavad n&otilde;uded </eesti>
<inglise>Requirements for companies inspecting roadworthiness of vehicles </inglise>
<eesti>(1) K&auml;esoleva seaduse &sect; 66 l&otilde;ikes 2 nimetatud &auml;ri&uuml;hingul peavad olema: </eesti>
<inglise>(1) Companies specified in subsection 66 (2) of this Act shall have: </inglise>
<eesti>1) tervisekaitsen&otilde;uetele ja kontrollitavatele s&otilde;idukitele vastavad ruumid ja territoorium v&otilde;i nende kasutamise v&otilde;imalus; </eesti>
<inglise>1) premises and territory which meet the health protection requirements and correspond to the vehicles to be inspected, or the possibility to use such premises and territory; </inglise>
<eesti>2) k&auml;esoleva seaduse &sect; 13 l&otilde;ike 3 kohaselt kehtestatud eeskirja n&otilde;uetele vastavad t&ouml;&ouml;tajad, seadmed, vahendid, m&otilde;&otilde;teriistad ja inventar. </eesti>
<inglise>2) employees, equipment, facilities, measuring instruments and inventory which meet the requirements of the rules established pursuant to subsection 13 (3) of this Act. </inglise>
<eesti>(2) Lepingut ei s&otilde;lmita &auml;ri&uuml;hinguga, kellega on viimase kahe aasta jooksul katkestatud k&auml;esoleva seaduse &sect; 66 l&otilde;ikes 2 nimetatud leping &auml;ri&uuml;hingu poolt toimepandud rikkumiste t&otilde;ttu. </eesti>
<inglise>(2) A contract shall not be entered into with a company if a contract specified in subsection 66 (2) of this Act has been terminated within the last two years due to violations committed by the company. </inglise>
<eesti>13. peat&uuml;kk </eesti>
<inglise>Chapter 13 </inglise>
<eesti>Maastikus&otilde;idukite liiklus </eesti>
<inglise>All-terrain Vehicles Traffic </inglise>
<eesti>&sect; 68. </eesti>
<inglise>&sect; 68. </inglise>
<eesti>Maastikus&otilde;iduk </eesti>
<inglise>All-terrain vehicles </inglise>
<eesti>K&auml;esoleva seaduse t&auml;henduses on maastikus&otilde;iduk mootori j&otilde;ul maastikul liikumiseks etten&auml;htud liiklusvahend, mis ei ole k&auml;esoleva seaduse t&auml;henduses mootors&otilde;iduk ja mis kuulub registreerimisele teede- ja sideministri m&auml;&auml;ratud korras. </eesti>
<inglise>For the purposes of this Act, an all-terrain vehicle is a power-driven vehicle which is designed to be driven off-road, which is not a motor vehicle within the meaning of this Act and which is subject to registration pursuant to the procedure specified by the Minister of Transport and Communications. </inglise>
<eesti>&sect; 69. </eesti>
<inglise>&sect; 69. </inglise>
<eesti>Maastikus&otilde;iduki registreerimine </eesti>
<inglise>Registration of all-terrain vehicles </inglise>
<eesti>(1) Registreerimisele kuuluvate maastikus&otilde;idukite loetelu kehtestab teede- ja sideminister. </eesti>
<inglise>(1) The list of all-terrain vehicles subject to registration shall be established by the Minister of Transport and Communications. </inglise>
<eesti>(2) Maastikus&otilde;iduki registreerimise ja tehnoseisundi kontrollimise eeskirjad ning n&otilde;uded maastikus&otilde;iduki tehnoseisundile ja varustusele kehtestab teede- ja sideminister. </eesti>
<inglise>(2) The rules for the registration and for the inspection of the roadworthiness of all-terrain vehicles and the requirements for the roadworthiness and equipment of all-terrain vehicles shall be established by the Minister of Transport and Communications. </inglise>
<eesti>(3) Registreeritud maastikus&otilde;idukil peab olema vastav riiklik registreerimism&auml;rk. </eesti>
<inglise>(3) Registered all-terrain vehicles shall bear the corresponding state registration plates. </inglise>
<eesti>(4) Kaitsej&otilde;udude maastikus&otilde;idukite registreerimise ja tehnoseisundi kontrollimise eeskirjad ning n&otilde;uded tehnoseisundile ja varustusele kehtestab kaitseminister. </eesti>
<inglise>(4) The rules for the registration and for the inspection of the roadworthiness of all-terrain vehicles of the Defence Forces and the requirements for the roadworthiness and equipment of such vehicles shall be established by the Minister of Defence. </inglise>
<eesti>&sect; 70. </eesti>
<inglise>&sect; 70. </inglise>
<eesti>Maastikus&otilde;idukiga liiklemine </eesti>
<inglise>All-terrain vehicle traffic </inglise>
<eesti>(1) Maastikus&otilde;idukiga ei v&otilde;i s&otilde;ita teel. </eesti>
<inglise>(1) All-terrain vehicles shall not be driven on roads. </inglise>
<eesti>(2) Maastikus&otilde;idukiga on lubatud s&otilde;ita teel j&otilde;gede, teede ja muude takistuste &uuml;letamiskohtades ning lumega kaetud teel, mis ei ole mootors&otilde;idukitele ajutiselt l&auml;bitav. </eesti>
<inglise>(2) It is permitted to drive all-terrain vehicles on roads at places where rivers, roads and other obstacles are crossed and on roads covered with snow which are temporarily inaccessible for motor vehicles. </inglise>
<eesti>Teel liikudes ei v&otilde;i s&otilde;ita kiiremini kui 50 kilomeetrit tunnis. </eesti>
<inglise>It is not permitted for all-terrain vehicles to be driven on roads faster than 50 kilometres per hour. </inglise>
<eesti>(3) Maastikul v&otilde;ib maastikus&otilde;idukiga s&otilde;ita v&otilde;i seda parkida &uuml;ksnes maavaldaja loal. </eesti>
<inglise>(3) All-terrain vehicles may be driven or parked off-road only with the permission of the land owner. </inglise>
<eesti>(4) K&auml;esoleva paragrahvi l&otilde;ikes 3 nimetatud luba ei n&otilde;uta: </eesti>
<inglise>(4) The permission specified in subsection (3) of this section is not required: </inglise>
<eesti>1) politsei-, tolli- ja piirivalvet&ouml;&ouml;tajatelt ameti&uuml;lesannete t&auml;itmisel; </eesti>
<inglise>1) from police, customs and Border Guard officials who are performing their duties; </inglise>
<eesti>2) haige toimetamisel haiglasse; </eesti>
<inglise>2) if a sick person is being taken to hospital; </inglise>
<eesti>3) tulekustutus- v&otilde;i p&auml;&auml;stet&ouml;&ouml;de tegijatelt; </eesti>
<inglise>3) from persons involved in fire extinguishing or rescue work; </inglise>
<eesti>4) muudel juhtudel, mis on seotud ameti&uuml;lesannete t&auml;itmisega, nagu elektri- ja sideliinide hooldus- ja parandust&ouml;&ouml;de tegemine jms. </eesti>
<inglise>4) in other cases related to the performance of duties, such as the provision of repair and maintenance services for power and communication lines, etc. </inglise>
<eesti>(5) Maastikus&otilde;idukit v&otilde;ib juhtida isik, kellel on mis tahes kategooria mootors&otilde;iduki juhtimise &otilde;igus. </eesti>
<inglise>(5) Persons who have the right to drive motor vehicles of any category may drive all-terrain vehicles. </inglise>
<eesti>Maastikus&otilde;iduki juhtimisel peab juhil olema kaasas juhiluba ja maastikus&otilde;iduki registreerimistunnistus. </eesti>
<inglise>When driving an all-terrain vehicle, a driver shall carry a driving licence and the registration certificate of the all-terrain vehicle. </inglise>
<eesti>(6) Maastikus&otilde;idukite liiklemise eeskirja kehtestab Vabariigi Valitsus. </eesti>
<inglise>(6) The rules for all-terrain vehicle traffic shall be established by the Government of the Republic. </inglise>
<eesti>Kohalikul omavalitsusel on &otilde;igus maastikus&otilde;idukite liiklemisele kehtestada t&auml;iendavaid n&otilde;udeid oma valla v&otilde;i linna territooriumil. </eesti>
<inglise>Each local government has the right to establish additional requirements for all-terrain vehicle traffic within the territory of its rural municipality or city. </inglise>
<eesti>14. peat&uuml;kk </eesti>
<inglise>Chapter 14 </inglise>
<eesti>Eris&auml;tted </eesti>
<inglise>Special Provisions </inglise>
<eesti>&sect; 71. </eesti>
<inglise>&sect; 71. </inglise>
<eesti>Eritalituse s&otilde;iduk </eesti>
<inglise>Emergency and road service vehicles </inglise>
<eesti>(1) Eritalituse s&otilde;iduk on: </eesti>
<inglise>(1) The following are emergency and road service vehicles: </inglise>
<eesti>1) kiireloomulisi ameti- v&otilde;i t&ouml;&ouml;&uuml;lesandeid t&auml;itev s&otilde;iduk (edaspidi alarms&otilde;iduk); </eesti>
<inglise>1) vehicles used to perform urgent functions or official duties (hereinafter emergency vehicles); </inglise>
<eesti>2) teehoiu&uuml;lesandeid ja teel m&ouml;&ouml;dap&auml;&auml;smatuid t&ouml;&ouml;&uuml;lesandeid t&auml;itev s&otilde;iduk (edaspidi hoolduss&otilde;iduk); </eesti>
<inglise>2) vehicles used to perform road management duties and unavoidable official duties on roads (hereinafter maintenance vehicles); </inglise>
<eesti>3) s&otilde;iduk, mida j&auml;litusametkonna v&otilde;i tema halduses oleva asutuse j&auml;litustegevusega tegelev t&ouml;&ouml;taja kasutab j&auml;litustegevuse seaduses (RT I 1994, 16, 290; 1995, 15, 173; 1996, 49, 955; 1997, 81, 1361; 93, 1557; 1998, 47, 698; 50, 753; 51, 756; 61, 981; 98/99, 1575; 101, 1663; 1999, 16, 271; 31, 425; 95, 845; 2000, 35, 222; 40, 251; 102, 671) etten&auml;htud j&auml;litustegevuse eri- v&otilde;i erandtoimingu teostamisel (edaspidi j&auml;lituss&otilde;iduk). </eesti>
<inglise>3) vehicles used by employees of a surveillance agency or an agency administered thereby who are engaged in surveillance activities upon conducting special or exceptional surveillance activities prescribed in the Surveillance Act (RT I 1994, 16, 290; 1995, 15, 173; 1996, 49, 955; 1997, 81, 1361; 93, 1557; 1998, 47, 698; 50, 753; 51, 756; 61, 981; 98/99, 1575; 101, 1663; 1999, 16, 271; 31, 425; 95, 845; 2000, 35, 222; 40, 251; 102, 671) (hereinafter surveillance vehicles). </inglise>
<eesti>(2) Alarms&otilde;iduki juht, kelle s&otilde;idukil on sisse l&uuml;litatud sinine vilkur koos erilise helisignaaliga v&otilde;i helisignaalita, v&otilde;ib ameti&uuml;lesannete t&auml;itmisel eirata k&auml;esoleva seaduse &sect; 47 l&otilde;igetes 1-4 nimetatud suurimat lubatud s&otilde;idukiirust. </eesti>
<inglise>(2) If the blue revolving or flashing lamps of an emergency vehicle are switched on, whether with or without a siren, the driver of the vehicle may ignore the speed limits specified in subsections 47 (1) -(4) of this Act upon performing his or her functions. </inglise>
<eesti>(3) J&auml;lituss&otilde;iduki juht v&otilde;ib k&auml;esoleva paragrahvi l&otilde;ike 1 punktis 3 nimetatud toimingute teostamisel eirata k&auml;esoleva seaduse &sect; 47 l&otilde;igetes 1-4 nimetatud suurimat lubatud s&otilde;idukiirust erisignaale kasutamata. </eesti>
<inglise>(3) The driver of a surveillance vehicle may ignore the speed limits specified in subsections 47 (1) -(4) of this Act without using a siren upon conducting the activities specified in clause (1) 3) of this section. </inglise>
<eesti>(4) Hoolduss&otilde;iduki juht, kelle s&otilde;idukil on sisse l&uuml;litatud kollane vilkur, v&otilde;ib t&ouml;&ouml;&uuml;lesannete t&auml;itmisel eirata k&auml;esoleva seaduse &sect; 3 l&otilde;ikes 1 nimetatud n&otilde;uet. </eesti>
<inglise>(4) If the yellow revolving or flashing lamps of a maintenance vehicle are switched on, the driver of the vehicle may ignore the requirement specified in subsection 3 (1) of this Act upon performing his or her official duties. </inglise>
<eesti>(5) Eritalituse s&otilde;iduki juht peab k&auml;esolevas paragrahvis nimetatud &otilde;igusi kasutades tagama liikluse ohutuse. </eesti>
<inglise>(5) Drivers of emergency and road service vehicles shall ensure that traffic safety is maintained when the rights specified in this section are exercised. </inglise>
<eesti>(6) Teised liiklejad peavad eritalituse s&otilde;idukile, millel on sisse l&uuml;litatud vilkur koos erisignaaliga v&otilde;i erisignaalita, ja sellise s&otilde;iduki poolt saadetavale s&otilde;idukile andma teed v&otilde;i vajaduse korral peatuma. </eesti>
<inglise>(6) Other road users shall give way to emergency and road service vehicles on which the revolving or flashing lamps are switched on, whether with or without a siren, and to vehicles accompanied by such vehicles, or shall stop if necessary. </inglise>
<eesti>(7) Eritalituse s&otilde;idukite loetelu, nende t&auml;histamise ja liiklemise korra kehtestab Vabariigi Valitsus. </eesti>
<inglise>(7) The list of emergency and road service vehicles, the procedure for their identification and the applicable traffic rules shall be established by the Government of the Republic. </inglise>
<eesti>&sect; 72. </eesti>
<inglise>&sect; 72. </inglise>
<eesti>Tramm </eesti>
<inglise>Trams </inglise>
<eesti>(1) Trammi ja selle haagise registreerimise ja tehnoseisundi kontrollimise eeskirjad ning n&otilde;uded trammi ja selle haagise tehnoseisundile ja varustusele kehtestab teede- ja sideminister. </eesti>
<inglise>(1) The rules for the registration and for the inspection of the fitness for service of trams and their trailers and the requirements for the roadworthiness and equipment of trams and their trailers shall be established by the Minister of Transport and Communications. </inglise>
<eesti>(2) Trammi v&otilde;ib juhtida isik, kellel on B-kategooria auto ja trammi juhtimise &otilde;igus ja kes on v&auml;hemalt 21-aastane. </eesti>
<inglise>(2) Persons who have the right to drive automobiles in category B and trams and who are of at least 21 years of age may drive trams. </inglise>
<eesti>Trammi juhtimist v&otilde;ib &otilde;ppida isik, kes on v&auml;hemalt 20,5 -aastane ja kellel on B-kategooria auto juhtimise &otilde;igus. </eesti>
<inglise>Persons who are of at least 20.5 years of age and who have the right to drive automobiles in category B may learn to drive a tram. </inglise>
<eesti>(3) Trammi juhtimise &otilde;iguse annab teede- ja sideministri m&auml;&auml;ratud asutus. </eesti>
<inglise>(3) The right to drive trams shall be granted by an agency designated by the Minister of Transport and Communications. </inglise>
<eesti>(4) N&otilde;uded trammijuhi terviseseisundile ja kutsesobivusele kehtestab sotsiaalminister. </eesti>
<inglise>(4) The requirements for the state of health and professional suitability of tram drivers shall be established by the Minister of Social Affairs. </inglise>
<eesti>Trammijuhi kvalifikatsioonin&otilde;uded, trammijuhi ettevalmistamise, eksamineerimise ja temale trammi juhtimise &otilde;iguse andmise eeskirjad ning trammi juhtimisel kohustuslikult kaasas olevate dokumentide loetelu kehtestab teede- ja sideminister. </eesti>
<inglise>The qualification requirements for tram drivers, the rules for the training and testing of tram drivers and for granting the right to drive trams thereto and the list of documents which are to be carried when driving a tram shall be established by the Minister of Transport and Communications. </inglise>
<eesti>(5) Trammi juhtimise &otilde;igus peatatakse, v&otilde;etakse &auml;ra, t&uuml;histatakse ja taastatakse k&auml;esolevas seaduses mootors&otilde;iduki juhtimise &otilde;iguse peatamise, &auml;rav&otilde;tmise, t&uuml;histamise ja taastamise kohta s&auml;testatu kohaselt. </eesti>
<inglise>(5) The right to drive trams shall be suspended, withdrawn, cancelled and restored pursuant to the provisions of this Act concerning suspension, withdrawal, cancellation and restoration of the right to drive motor vehicles. </inglise>
<eesti>&sect; 73. </eesti>
<inglise>&sect; 73. </inglise>
<eesti>Erin&otilde;uded mootors&otilde;idukitega seotud &otilde;igustoimingutele </eesti>
<inglise>Special requirements for legal acts relating to motor vehicles </inglise>
<eesti>Kui kohalik omavalitsus on kehtestanud mootors&otilde;idukimaksu v&otilde;i kui mootors&otilde;iduki eest tuleb tasuda raskeveokimaksu, ei saa vastava maksu tasumist t&otilde;endavat dokumenti esitamata: </eesti>
<inglise>If a local government establishes a motor vehicle tax or if a heavy goods vehicle tax is to be paid for a motor vehicle, it is not permitted to perform the following legal acts without submitting a document certifying payment of the corresponding tax: </inglise>
<eesti>1) teha muudatusi mootors&otilde;iduki registreerimisandmetes; </eesti>
<inglise>1) amendment of the registration information of the motor vehicle; </inglise>
<eesti>2) kustutada mootors&otilde;idukit registrist v&otilde;&otilde;randamise eesm&auml;rgil; </eesti>
<inglise>2) deletion of the motor vehicle from the register for the purpose of its transfer; </inglise>
<eesti>3) v&auml;ljastada esmakordselt riiklikku registrisse kantud mootors&otilde;iduki omanikule v&otilde;i tema esindajale mootors&otilde;iduki riiklikku registreerimistunnistust ega riiklikku registreerimism&auml;rki. </eesti>
<inglise>3) issue of a state registration certificate or a state registration plate for the motor vehicle to the owner or representative of the owner of the vehicle when the vehicle is entered in the state register for the first time. </inglise>
<eesti>&sect; 74. </eesti>
<inglise>&sect; 74. </inglise>
<eesti>Seaduse laienemine v&auml;lismaalasele ja v&auml;lismaal registreeritud s&otilde;idukile </eesti>
<inglise>Extension of Act to aliens and vehicles registered abroad </inglise>
<eesti>K&auml;esolev seadus laieneb Eesti territooriumil viibivale v&auml;lismaalasest liiklejale ja v&auml;lismaal registreeritud s&otilde;idukile, kui konventsioonide v&otilde;i rahvusvaheliste lepingutega ei ole ette n&auml;htud teisiti. </eesti>
<inglise>This Act extends to foreign road users and vehicles registered abroad which are in the territory of Estonia unless a convention or international agreement prescribes otherwise. </inglise>
<eesti>15. peat&uuml;kk </eesti>
<inglise>Chapter 15 </inglise>
<eesti>Rakenduss&auml;tted </eesti>
<inglise>Implementing Provisions </inglise>
<eesti>&sect; 75. </eesti>
<inglise>&sect; 75. </inglise>
<eesti>T&auml;htajata juhilubade kehtivus </eesti>
<inglise>Validity of driving licences issued for unspecified term </inglise>
<eesti>T&auml;htajata auto- ja mootorrattajuhiload, mis on v&auml;lja antud Eestis elavatele isikutele Eestis v&otilde;i endise N&otilde;ukogude Liidu territooriumil, kehtivad 2001. aasta 30. juunini. </eesti>
<inglise>Automobile and motorcycle driving licences which have been issued for an unspecified term in Estonia or in the territory of the former Soviet Union to persons residing in Estonia are valid until 30 June 2001. </inglise>
<eesti>&sect; 76. </eesti>
<inglise>&sect; 76. </inglise>
<eesti>Mootors&otilde;iduki registreerimisdokumentide kehtivus </eesti>
<inglise>Validity of registration documents of motor vehicles </inglise>
<eesti>Eestis enne 1993. aasta 1. novembrit v&auml;ljaantud mootors&otilde;idukite ja nende haagiste tehnilised passid, tehnilised talongid ja registreerimistunnistused kehtivad 2001. aasta 30. juunini. </eesti>
<inglise>Technical passports, registration cards and registration certificates issued in Estonia for motor vehicles and their trailers before 1 November 1993 are valid until 30 June 2001. </inglise>
<eesti>Kui 2002. aasta 1. jaanuariks ei ole nimetatud dokumendid uuendatud, kustutatakse mootors&otilde;iduk ja selle haagis liiklusregistrist. </eesti>
<inglise>If these documents are not renewed by 1 January 2002, the relevant motor vehicle and trailer shall be deleted from the traffic register. </inglise>
<eesti>&sect; 77. </eesti>
<inglise>&sect; 77. </inglise>
<eesti>Mootors&otilde;idukijuhi &otilde;petaja kvalifikatsioonin&otilde;uete rakendumine </eesti>
<inglise>Application of qualification requirements for driving instructors </inglise>
<eesti>K&auml;esoleva seaduse &sect; 36 l&otilde;ikes 2 nimetatud n&otilde;uded mootors&otilde;idukijuhi &otilde;petaja kvalifikatsioonile rakenduvad 2002. aasta 1. juulil. </eesti>
<inglise>The requirements for the qualifications of driving instructors specified in subsection 36 (2) of this Act apply as of 1 July 2002. </inglise>
<eesti>&sect; 78. </eesti>
<inglise>&sect; 78. </inglise>
<eesti>Varasema &otilde;igusakti kehtetuks tunnistamine </eesti>
<inglise>Repeal of earlier legislation </inglise>
