<eesti>Mootors&otilde;idukite kategooriad vastavalt juhtimis&otilde;igusele </eesti>
<inglise>Categories of Motor Vehicles according to Right to Drive </inglise>
<eesti>K&auml;esolevas seaduses tuleb termineid m&otilde;ista allj&auml;rgnevalt: </eesti>
<inglise>In this Act, the following terms are used: </inglise>
<eesti>Auto on s&otilde;itjate v&otilde;i veoste veoks v&otilde;i s&otilde;idukite haakes vedamiseks v&otilde;i erit&ouml;&ouml;de tegemiseks etten&auml;htud v&auml;hemalt neljarattaline mootors&otilde;iduk, mille valmistajakiirus &uuml;letab 25 km/h. </eesti>
<inglise>An automobile is a motor vehicle with at least four wheels which is designed for the carriage of passengers or goods or to be towed when coupled to vehicles, or for being used in specific work applications, and the design speed of which is more than 25 kph. </inglise>
<eesti>Autoks loetakse ka kolmerattalist mootors&otilde;idukit ja elektrikontaktliiniga &uuml;hendatud r&ouml;&ouml;basteta s&otilde;idukit. </eesti>
<inglise>Three-wheeled motor vehicles and vehicles which are connected to an electric conductor and not rail-borne are also deemed to be automobiles. </inglise>
<eesti>Autoks ei loeta mopeedi, mootorratast, traktorit ega liikurmasinat. </eesti>
<inglise>Mopeds, motorcycles, tractors and non-road mobile machinery are not deemed to be automobiles. </inglise>
<eesti>Autorong on autost ja &uuml;hest v&otilde;i enamast haagisest koostatud s&otilde;idukite kombinatsioon. </eesti>
<inglise>A road train is a combination of vehicles including an automobile and one or more trailers. </inglise>
<eesti>Eriv&otilde;imsus on mootori v&otilde;imsuse ja s&otilde;iduki t&uuml;himassi suhe. </eesti>
<inglise>Effective power is the ratio of the engine power to the unladen mass of a vehicle. </inglise>
<eesti>Haagis on mootors&otilde;idukiga haakes liikumiseks valmistatud v&otilde;i selleks kohandatud s&otilde;iduk. </eesti>
<inglise>A trailer is a vehicle manufactured to be towed when coupled to a motor vehicle or a vehicle adapted thereto. </inglise>
<eesti>Kerghaagis on haagis, mille registrimass ei &uuml;leta 750 kg. </eesti>
<inglise>A light trailer is a trailer with a permissible maximum mass not exceeding 750 kg. </inglise>
<eesti>Liikurmasin on ratastel liikuv teatud kindla t&ouml;&ouml; tegemiseks etten&auml;htud mootors&otilde;iduk, mille suurim valmistajakiirus &uuml;letab 6 km/h, kuid ei &uuml;leta 40 km/h. </eesti>
<inglise>Non-road mobile machinery is a motor vehicle on wheels designed for carrying out specific work and with a design speed of more than 6 kph but not more than 40 kph. </inglise>
<eesti>Liikurmasinaks ei loeta auto alusel valmistatud erit&ouml;&ouml;masinat. </eesti>
<inglise>Vehicles designed for specific work applications which are manufactured on the basis of automobiles are not deemed to be non-road mobile machinery. </inglise>
<eesti>Mootorratas on k&uuml;lghaagisega v&otilde;i k&uuml;lghaagiseta kaherattaline mootors&otilde;iduk, mille sisep&otilde;lemismootori t&ouml;&ouml;maht on &uuml;le 50 cm (3) v&otilde;i valmistajakiirus on &uuml;le 45 km/h. </eesti>
<inglise>A motorcycle is a two-wheeled motor vehicle with or without a sidecar which has an internal combustion engine with a capacity exceeding 50 cm (3) and the design speed of which is more than 45 kph. </inglise>
<eesti>Mopeed on kahe- v&otilde;i kolmerattaline s&otilde;iduk, mille sisep&otilde;lemismootori t&ouml;&ouml;maht ei &uuml;leta 50 cm (3) ja valmistajakiirus ei &uuml;leta 45 km/h. </eesti>
<inglise>A moped is a two-wheeled or three-wheeled vehicle which has an internal combustion engine with a capacity not exceeding 50 cm (3) and the design speed of which is not more than 45 kph. </inglise>
<eesti>Ratastraktor on mootors&otilde;iduk, millel on rattad ja v&auml;hemalt kaks telge ja mille suurim valmistajakiirus &uuml;letab 6 km/h, kuid ei &uuml;leta 40 km/h. </eesti>
<inglise>A wheeled tractor is a motor vehicle which has wheels and at least two axles and the maximum design speed of which is more than 6 kph but not more than 40 kph. </inglise>
<eesti>Ratastraktori p&otilde;hifunktsiooniks on sellel paikneva v&otilde;i sellega haakes oleva masina v&otilde;i riistaga t&ouml;&ouml;tamine, paikse masina k&auml;itamine v&otilde;i haagise vedamine. </eesti>
<inglise>The main function of a wheeled tractor is to work with a machine or equipment which is located thereon or coupled thereto, to operate a stationary machine or tow a trailer. </inglise>
<eesti>Registrimass on juhi, s&otilde;itjate ja veosega t&auml;isvarustuses s&otilde;idukile registreerimisel m&auml;&auml;ratud suurim mass, mis ei v&otilde;i &uuml;letada valmistaja lubatud suurimat massi. </eesti>
<inglise>Permissible maximum mass is the maximum mass determined upon registration for a fully equipped vehicle together with its driver, passengers and cargo, which shall not exceed the maximum mass permitted by the manufacturer. </inglise>
<eesti>Tegelik mass on s&otilde;iduki mass antud hetkel koos juhi, s&otilde;itjate ja veosega. </eesti>
<inglise>Laden mass is the mass of a vehicle at a given moment together with its driver, passengers and cargo. </inglise>
<eesti>T&uuml;himass on juhi, s&otilde;itjate ja veoseta t&auml;isvarustuses s&otilde;iduki mass, mille on m&auml;&auml;ranud valmistaja. </eesti>
<inglise>Unladen mass is the mass determined by the manufacturer, of a fully equipped vehicle without a driver, passengers or cargo. </inglise>
